author: {'steamid': '76561198170100746', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 12, 'playtime_forever': 518, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 502, 'last_played': 1708494896}
review:
Maybe someday Steam will make an exception to the 2 hour gameplay refund rule. If only I hadn't fallen asleep drunk playing this, I would have my $14.99 back to spend on something worthwhile.

This is nothing like I thought it would be, guess a lesson is learned not to blindly purchase a game a decade late just to "finally play it".

This game is barren. The things that are there are very early physics sandbox levels of entertaining and last only a minute.

If I could, in my roughly two hours of gameplay, recall any part of the game as unique into a list it would be as follows:
Fly a blimp
Fly airplane with machine gun (there's nothing to shoot at)
I sat here for five mins with no new thoughts on what I liked so I gave up

Here's a list of shit I hate now lol:
Walking is SLOW
Can't run for more than 5 seconds without falling down and farting (this is a mechanic not a quirk of the physics engine)
It's hard to leave the barren starting area and then when you do it's even MORE barren
Cars are especially slow given the expanse of wasteland you are given
If you are in a body of water for more than 30 seconds you are surrounded by alligators or sharks that swarm and eat you (this is terrible for exploring as spawn points are tens of minutes of walking away from one another)
Probably more that I can't put into words or I am bored

goodbye i love you all please dont spend money on this unless it's a DEEP sale I really can't recommend this to ANYONE

author: {'steamid': '76561198859317636', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 5, 'playtime_forever': 6643, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 6493, 'last_played': 1705895986}
review:
Ever since you developers abruptly removed the "Legacy" version of the game, I have eagerly awaited the moment to express my discontent through this review. As a once-loyal fan of your game, the removal of the original version in favor of the glitch-ridden V2 and V3 versions has left me profoundly disappointed. Your decision to effectively eliminate the authentic gaming experience from Steam has cast a shadow over my enthusiasm for the game.

The "Legacy" version held a special place in the hearts of many players, offering a unique and enjoyable gaming atmosphere. Its removal has not only erased cherished memories but also replaced them with versions plagued by technical issues. The transition to V2 and V3 has been far from seamless, and the absence of the original game has created a void that newer iterations fail to fill adequately. The decision to discontinue the Legacy version seems to have sacrificed the essence of what made the game beloved among its dedicated community.

Until there is a reconsideration and the reinstatement of the Legacy version, I must regretfully announce my departure from the game. This move represents not only my personal dissatisfaction but also a sentiment shared by numerous players who yearn for the return of the authentic gaming experience. It is my hope that you, as developers, will take into account the voices of your loyal fan base and work towards a solution that revives the essence of the game we once held dear. Goodbye for now, with the hope that future decisions align more closely with the desires of the community.

review: Amazing Frog is a truly exceptional game that captivates players with its unique blend of humor, creativity, and open-world chaos. The game's distinct charm lies in its ability to seamlessly combine a lighthearted, physics-based sandbox environment with an array of absurd challenges and comical characters. From navigating the quirky landscape of Swindon to experimenting with the plethora of gadgets and vehicles, players are constantly immersed in an unpredictable and entertaining experience. The game's open-world design encourages exploration and discovery, offering a plethora of hidden gems and unexpected surprises around every corner. Moreover, Amazing Frog's multiplayer feature enhances the overall enjoyment, allowing friends to join in the madness together. With its offbeat humor, imaginative gameplay, and the sheer joy of discovering the unexpected, Amazing Frog stands out as a genuinely delightful and engaging gaming experience.

review:
Can't recommend this game. It is not user friendly. I've had this game for a good while before a major update, due to which, I lost all my progress (weapons, jetpacks, etc.). It only left me the character costumes I had previously found. You cannot save your progress when you're attempting to collect things like gold and silver trophies trash/lost mail while progressing towards the "key-to-the-city" achievement.  Also, character movement leaves something to be desired, the character keeps falling down. The story concept is kind-of fun, but making progress in the game is for me an exercise in frustration. I think I'll "retire" this one.
:steamthumbsdown:

review: It's sad, I'm sure when this game came out it was tons of fun, but now it's just a desolate wasteland. Nowhere to go, nothing to do, and no one else playing. I wandered around in the walled area for a good hour, and it was just... boring? Sure bouncing on things and watching the physics simulator act silly was fun, but it got old really quick. I looked up how to get outside and once I did... oh man, was it so much worse. Just giant expanses of nothing but trees. No background music for ambiance either, and no objects to interact with. It was quite dystopian. What a shame.

Its always been great but i just want this small little thing for the settings, not much to ask eh? I definitely recommend this, u should get it, its only like 16 bucks out of ur account, ive bought a pen that lasted less than a week more expensive than this.

review: this game is a wacky open-world physics-based game that offers a unique and hilarious gaming experience. it takes place in the town of swindon, where you control a frog with a range of absurd abilities. the game is filled with quirky challenges, humorous interactions, and a vast sandbox environment to explore. the gameplay mechanics are intentionally wonky, leading to unpredictable and often hilarious outcomes. the graphics may not be top-notch, but they perfectly complement the game's offbeat style. with its multiplayer mode, you can even enjoy the chaos with friends. overall, amazing frog is a delightful and entertaining game that will keep you laughing and entertained for hours.

author: {'steamid': '76561198953992606', 'num_games_owned': 117, 'num_reviews': 30, 'playtime_forever': 50, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 50, 'last_played': 1683602601}
review: I personally just couldn't get into this game. I'm sure that it's probably better when played with friends but for a mostly solo player it just lacks a lot of what could drive me to play. The world feels a bit empty to me (even for a sandbox game) and, although there is quite a lot of things to do between the multiple versions of the game, I just didn't come to care enough about any of it to keep exploring it. I'm honestly a little bit surprised about the very positive rating that it has but there must just be something about it that I'm missing since there seems to be a loyal fan group and people really do seem to like it for whatever reason. As for the good it's got interesting game physics and some pretty silly but funny humor which I thought worked pretty well with the world that they've created. I still wish the developer(s) good luck in the future with their game and hope it continues to grow over time. If you read any reviews about missing/removed content just know that there are (as I mentioned earlier) a few different launch options that are different versions of the game and some versions have things that others don't so try them all out before giving up on it like I eventually did.

author: {'steamid': '76561199157178911', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 2, 'playtime_forever': 4234, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 3050, 'last_played': 1709992324}
review:
Игра мне очень понравилась!! Она так и смешная, так и очень интересная. Можно и побаловаться бегая по городу и другим местам, а можно и выполнять различные задания и квесты. Я вообще где-то в 2018 скачал эту с пиратского сайта (жалею, что не купил сразу) и думал, что она просто развлекалка и создана для того, чтобы чисто поржать. но нет, тут много чего можно сделать и многим можно заняться: от собирания мусора в мусорные баки до убийства Мегалодона в море. Ну, впрочем, каждый раз когда я играл скучно становилось максимально редко. я всегда придумывал что натворить.
Чуть не забыл сказать.. если стало очень скучно, то можно позвать друга / друзей поиграть вместе, так намного веселее и смешнее. Короче, если вы хотите угарать как сумасшедшие, творить полный хаос и заниматься другими приколюшками, то эта игра для вас. Игра на любителя.

author: {'steamid': '76561199122280341', 'num_games_owned': 740, 'num_reviews': 24, 'playtime_forever': 248, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 244, 'last_played': 1710704181}
review:
Si buscas un juego divertido y diferente, no puedes perderte Amazing Frog. Este juego te ofrece una experiencia única y emocionante, en la que puedes explorar el mundo abierto de Swindon como una rana. Con una gran variedad de actividades, desafíos y objetos para descubrir, Amazing Frog te mantendrá entretenido durante horas.

Los gráficos y la física de este juego son impresionantes, ofreciendo un nivel de realismo que te sumergirá en el juego y te hará sentir como si estuvieras realmente en Swindon. Además, la personalización de la rana y la capacidad de jugar en modo multijugador con amigos hacen que la experiencia de juego sea aún más divertida.

En resumen, Amazing Frog es un juego muy recomendable para aquellos que buscan algo diferente y divertido. Con su amplio mundo abierto, gráficos impresionantes y una gran cantidad de actividades y desafíos para explorar, este juego ofrece una experiencia de juego única y emocionante que no te decepcionará. ¡No dudes en darle una oportunidad!

author: {'steamid': '76561198312507095', 'num_games_owned': 16, 'num_reviews': 12, 'playtime_forever': 6454, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 6454, 'last_played': 1678147891}
review:
For me, Grand Theft Auto V’s extraordinary scope is summed up in two favourite moments. One is from a mid-game mission in which I flew a plane into another plane, fought the crew, hijacked the thing, and then parachuted out and watched it crash into the sea to escape death at the hands of incoming military fighter jets. Another time, whilst driving around in an off-road buggy, I got distracted by something that looked like a path up one of the San Andreas mountains. Turns out it was a path, and I spent 15 minutes following to the summit, where I nearly ran over a group of hikers. “Typical!” one of them yelled at me, as if he nearly gets run over by a rogue ATV on top of a mountain every time he goes on a hike.

I could go on like this for ages. GTA V has an abundance of such moments, big and small, that make San Andreas – the city of Los Santos and its surrounding areas – feel like a living world where anything can happen. It both gives you tremendous freedom to explore an astonishingly well-realised world and tells a story that’s gripping, thrilling, and darkly comic. It is a leap forward in narrative sophistication for the series, and there’s no mechanical element of the gameplay that hasn’t been improved over Grand Theft Auto IV. It’s immediately noticeable that the cover system is more reliable and the auto-aim less touchy. The cars handle less like their tires are made of butter and stick better to the road, though their exaggerated handling still leaves plenty of room for spectacular wipeouts. And at long last, Rockstar has finally slain one of its most persistent demons, mission checkpointing, ensuring that you never have to do a long, tedious drive six times when you repeatedly fail a mission ever again.  Grand Theft Auto V is also an intelligent, wickedly comic, and bitingly relevant commentary on contemporary, post-economic crisis America. Everything about it drips satire: it rips into the Millennial generation, celebrities, the far right, the far left, the middle class, the media... Nothing is safe from Rockstar’s sharp tongue, including modern video games. One prominent supporting character spends most of his time in his room shouting sexual threats at people on a headset whilst playing a first-person shooter called Righteous Slaughter (“Rated PG – pretty much the same as the last game.”) It’s not exactly subtle – he literally has the word “Entitled” tattooed on his neck, and the in-game radio and TV’s outright piss-takes don’t leave much to the imagination – but it is often extremely funny, and sometimes provocative with it. Grand Theft Auto’s San Andreas is a fantasy, but the things it satirises – greed, corruption, hypocrisy, the abuse of power – are all very real. If GTA IV was a targeted assassination of the American dream, GTA V takes aim at the modern American reality. The attention to detail that goes into making its world feel alive and believable is also what makes its satire so biting.

 The satire is helped by integration of modern life into the game world. Every character revolves around their smartphone – it’s used to trade stocks, call up friends to meet up and send emails. There’s a great Facebook spoof, Life Invader, on the in-game Interne, with the slogan “Where Your Personal Information Becomes A Marketing Profile (That We Can Sell)”. You’ll hear adverts for preposterous parodic TV shows that you can actually watch on your TV at home, optionally whilst enjoying a toke. It might not be realistic, but it definitely feels authentic.  It’s worth mentioning that when it comes to sex, drugs, and violence, GTA V pushes boundaries much further than ever before. If the morality police were worried about Hot Coffee, there’s a lot here that will provoke moral hysteria. It’s deliciously subversive, and firmly tongue in cheek... but once or twice, it pushes the boundaries of taste, too. There’s one particular scene, a torture scene in which you have no choice but to actively participate, that I found so troubling that I had difficulty playing it; even couched in obvious criticism of the US government’s recourse to torture post 9/11, it’s a shocking moment that will attract justified controversy. It brings to mind Call of Duty: Modern Warfare 2’s No Russian mission, except worse, and without the option to skip over it. Some other stuff, like the ever-present prostitution and extensive strip-club minigames, feels like it’s there just because it can be rather than because it has anything to say.  But, it involves more frogs and farting.

author: {'steamid': '76561198857400119', 'num_games_owned': 10, 'num_reviews': 1, 'playtime_forever': 12401, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 9862, 'last_played': 1705451484}
review:
( Before you continue reading, my review of the game ONLY APPLIES TO THE LEGACY VERSION. I play on mac, and V3 runs very slowly, and even crashes when trying to do things such as drive. V2 also crashes before I can reach the main menu. )

This game is amazing. I got steam in 2018 just for this game, and I'm glad that I did. I've recently started using steam again, and have re-discovered the awesomeness that is this game.

It is almost impossible to get bored in this game, as it's amount of content is astounding. There is so much to do, i'd be here for hours trying to type a third of everything possible in-game. The game is incredibly comical, going as far as to implement humor into it's loading screens. Want to go to the moon dressed as Darth Vader? You can! Want to go swimming in a completely, 100 percent shark free lake? You can! Want to do the police department's job better then they can? Go on, arrest the evil-doers of Swindon, maybe you'll even get rewarded after arresting a certain number of criminals ;).

One thing that is a big deterrent to many people is the price. 16 dollars is quite pricy. If you have the time to explore all of the game's features, and the money to purchase it, I'd recommend this to you. It gives a great laugh, a great adventure, and an overall great time.

review:
Jogo muito bom, é aquele tipo de jogo de quem gosta de mundo aberto VAI AMAR, o mundo dele é GIGANTE tendo muitas coisas pra fazer. Mas com o tempo o jogo começa a ficar meio chato e enjoado...Porém tem uma solução AMIGOS, tente chamar alguns amigos pra jogar pelo remote play que vai por mim o jogo fica muito divertido.


Gráficos:Normais, não são TÃAAO detalhados mas também não são mal feitos

Diversão: O jogo é bem divertido no inicio tendo muitas coisas pra fazer como por exemplo liberar o espaço matar o tubarão gigante e etc

CONCLUSÃO: Não recomendo comprar no momento, espere uma promoção que fica perfeito

review:
very fun game, probably not for those who get frustrated easily though, patience is key, you better get used to attempting to get back up for the 5th time in a row

The legacy version of the game, while being poorly optimised, has a lot to do and is in general very fun making up a large portion of my nostalgia now

The newer version when it first came out had literally nothing to do, and while I understand they have been adding stuff it just isn't on the same level as the original, yet is much better in terms of visuals and performance as well as just being less of a hassle to work with

author: {'steamid': '76561198164331724', 'num_games_owned': 123, 'num_reviews': 130, 'playtime_forever': 15098, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 13639, 'last_played': 1703493221}
review: Amazing Frog?, who knew a small game like this could be something so special. Amazing Frog? is one of those games where you just tried out as a joke, but really it turned out to be something much more incredible than that. It really captures the essence of Grand Theft Auto V and well, makes it better in every way possible. You don't need a big budget or a big game to do that. Though with this games updates it has gotten very big. This game was apart of my childhood and forever will be, so it has a very special place in my heart, hence why I love it so very much. There is so much nostalgia behind this little game. It is the funniest, stupidest, silliest and en-joyful  games you could ever play in an entire gaming career. However it makes for an unbeatable multiplayer experience and is one of the best games ever to date. It also updates quite frequently, showing how much passion Gaz and Hal have for this incredible indie game. 9.5/10

review:
個人的には見慣れているドアとトランポリンで大ジャンプできて滑走が出来るレガシーのほうが好きです
人間サイズのカエルが街でぶっ飛んだりバグったり豚と散歩したり銃ぶっ放したり、よく街で見る光景ですね（大嘘）
操作性はあまりよくなくすぐおならをして転んだりするのですが、それ以外は基本的に高評価です
「昔出来た滑走やドア大ジャンプもできなくなっている」ということを言っている人もいましたがレガシーを選択すれば今まで通りのアメイジングなゲームを楽しむことができます！

author: {'steamid': '76561199225366857', 'num_games_owned': 10, 'num_reviews': 3, 'playtime_forever': 73, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 73, 'last_played': 1673052219}
review:
This game truly is the definition of derp. The farts are acutely disgusting, with a hint of stench and a green
cloud that envelops. The citizens stumble around and fall over at the drop of a hat. There are weapons in the
game, ranging from water guns to automatic rifles. These are ridiculous to consider, because a frog could
never wield these weapons. The multiple different animals are also derpy too, since the sharks look goofy
and unrealistic. There are also giant ants, which is weird since ants are very small, providing good humor in
irony. The multiple methods of movement only add to the silliness of it all. You can either slide around on the
ground, fly through the air, or walk around and occasionally fall over from a fart. These are all very silly since
a typical frog cannot do any of these things. For he is not a regular frog, he is the AMAZING frog.

review:
SIM! Eu sei que tenho poucas horas de jogo, mas jogo esse jogo desde 2016 mais ou menos, um jogo de infância pra mim e por conta disso esse jogo tem uma grande importância pra mim. Enfim... Como eu sei que vocês querem saber se o jogo é bom, ai vai umas coisinhas que pode fazer você comprar esse maravilhoso jogo: 

1- Com amigos você pode ter uma asfixia de tanto rir que talvez possa levar você ao hospital ._.

2- Jogo bom pra passar o tempo

3- Jogo com varias referências de personagens de desenhos animados e etc

4- Com amigos da pra fazer uma história que vale Oscar se tivesse nos cinemas kakaakak

5- Jogo não enjoa fácil (eu desde 2016 mais ou menos comecei a jogar o jogo e até hoje não consegui enjoar dessa obra de arte)

6- Se você ajudar a divulgar esse jogo gravando muitos videos sobre ele, se os videos tiverem pegando muitas views e a Fayju (desenvolvedora do jogo) ver isso, ela coloca um carro com seu nome na placa! SONHOOO

7- Mundo aberto pra você explorar tuuuuudo!

8- Muitas skins e Easter eggs escondidas em qualquer canto do mapa

9- Jogo muito engraçado e bom (melhor ainda com amigos, familiares e etc)

10 - Além do mundo aberto normal em si, tem como ir pro espaço, pra um esgoto cheio de zumbis famintos e tals

SO COMPRA MANO! VALE MUITO APENA! TO AMANDO <3 OBRIGADO POR ESSA OBRA DE ARTE FAYJU!!!!

author: {'steamid': '76561198176893635', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 9, 'playtime_forever': 5893, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 5893, 'last_played': 1668469156}
review: Eu sou um pai de 45 anos, provavelmente uma das pessoas mais velhas a jogar este jogo. Sou pai solteiro criando meu filho, que agora tem 14 anos. Meu filho ganhou este jogo no Natal de 2021 de seu tio, então o instalamos em seu computador e ele começou a jogar. Até o final da semana ele tinha 24 horas neste jogo. Isso foi horrível para mim, pois já era difícil encontrar maneiras de passar o tempo com meu filho, pois ele está sempre com os amigos ou apenas assistindo ao YouTube. Então eu decidi fazer uma conta no Steam e pegar esse jogo para ver se eu poderia jogar ao lado dele. Eu comprei o jogo, escolhi minha skin e mundo e comecei a jogar, mas eu estava preso no que você deveria fazer. Pedi ajuda ao meu filho e ele organizou um jogo para eu participar. Adorei, pois foi o melhor momento que passei com meu filho desde que minha esposa morreu. Desde então, esse jogo aproximou eu e meu filho novamente e agora passamos um tempo juntos fora de casa também. Este jogo me lembrou que há diversão em tudo, e trouxe muitas lembranças felizes para mim e meu filho.

review: Eu sou um pai de 45 anos, provavelmente uma das pessoas mais velhas a jogar este jogo. Sou pai solteiro criando meu filho, que agora tem 14 anos. Meu filho ganhou este jogo no Natal de 2021 de seu tio, então o instalamos em seu computador e ele começou a jogar. Até o final da semana ele tinha 24 horas neste jogo. Isso foi horrível para mim, pois já era difícil encontrar maneiras de passar o tempo com meu filho, pois ele está sempre com os amigos ou apenas assistindo ao YouTube. Então eu decidi fazer uma conta no Steam e pegar esse jogo para ver se eu poderia jogar ao lado dele. Eu comprei o jogo, escolhi minha skin e mundo e comecei a jogar, mas eu estava preso no que você deveria fazer. Pedi ajuda ao meu filho e ele organizou um jogo para eu participar. Adorei, pois foi o melhor momento que passei com meu filho desde que minha esposa morreu. Desde então, esse jogo aproximou eu e meu filho novamente e agora passamos um tempo juntos fora de casa também. Este jogo me lembrou que há diversão em tudo, e trouxe muitas lembranças felizes para mim e meu filho.

review:
## Pontos positivos

- É tipo GTA só que mais simples e engraçado
- Tem um mapa gigante, a cidade é apenas uma fração dele, você precisa sair dela para explorar o resto
- Da pra jogar em modo multiplayer local
- Muitas coisas divertidas para fazer, essas coisas não estão explícitas, então você precisa ser curioso, explorar bem a cidade
- Você compra e ganha as 3 versões do jogo, Legacy, Remastered e Respawned

## Pontos negativos

- 3 versões do mesmo jogo. Para mim isso foi bem confuso no começo, mas no site do desenvolvedor ele explica melhor. Se você quer uma experiência mais completa recomendo jogar a v1(legacy) ou v2(remastered), a v3 ainda esta muito crua e falta otimizações
- Se você esta correndo, a cada alguns passos dado você peida e cai no chão. Eu sinceramente achei isso engraçado no começo, mas passa um tempo e começa a encher o saco, deveria ao menos ter a opção de desabilitar isso, mas não é nada que atrapalhe a gameplay no geral

review:
Amazing Frog: A Whimsical and Hilarious Sandbox Adventure

Introduction:
Amazing Frog, developed by Fayju and available on Steam, is a unique and delightfully absurd sandbox game that defies conventions and embraces pure fun. In this review, we dive into the quirky world of Amazing Frog and explore why it has gained a dedicated fanbase and a reputation for its offbeat humor and chaotic gameplay.

Graphics and Visual Style (8/10):
While Amazing Frog's graphics may not boast photorealistic visuals, its intentionally simplistic and cartoonish art style perfectly complements the game's lighthearted and humorous tone. The vibrant and colorful open-world environment of Swindonshire is filled with amusing details and unexpected surprises, adding to the overall charm of the game.

Gameplay and Freedom (9/10):
What sets Amazing Frog apart is its emphasis on player freedom and experimentation. As a frog let loose in the open-world sandbox, you can explore Swindonshire at your own pace, interacting with objects and causing hilarious chaos. From performing absurd stunts and driving vehicles to engaging in comical battles with fellow frogs, the possibilities for outrageous and unpredictable gameplay moments are endless.

Humor and Satire (10/10):
One of the game's strongest aspects is its exceptional sense of humor. Amazing Frog embraces its absurdity and revels in ridiculous situations, providing players with constant moments of laughter. From slapstick comedy and physics-based mayhem to clever pop culture references and witty Easter eggs, the game is a comedic goldmine that keeps players entertained and engaged.

Multiplayer and Social Experience (8/10):
While Amazing Frog can be enjoyed in single-player mode, the true charm of the game shines when played with friends. Whether you're exploring Swindonshire together, engaging in hilarious races, or engaging in spontaneous shenanigans, the multiplayer aspect enhances the fun and laughter. The game's cooperative and competitive multiplayer modes offer hours of shared enjoyment and memorable experiences.

Updates and Community Interaction (9/10):
The developers of Amazing Frog have demonstrated their commitment to the game and its community through regular updates and content additions. They actively engage with the player base, listening to feedback and implementing improvements. This dedication has fostered a positive and enthusiastic community that actively contributes to the game's evolution through mods and user-generated content.

Conclusion:
Amazing Frog is a one-of-a-kind sandbox adventure that embraces silliness, humor, and unrestricted freedom. Its charming visual style, hilarious gameplay, and multiplayer interactions make it a standout experience for those seeking laughter and lighthearted entertainment. Whether you're looking to explore a whimsical open world, engage in wacky stunts, or simply embrace the chaos, Amazing Frog delivers an unforgettable and endlessly enjoyable experience that will keep you coming back for more.

review:
Ride a pig.

Get eaten by a zombie.

Release the zombie pig.

Run with an RPG, trip, then shoot it on accident and blow yourself up.

Go to the moon.

Piss off Shai-Hulud

Get eaten by giant ants.

Perform shoddy electrical repair.

Go to the beach. And regret it.

Go to the lake. And regret it.

Flush everything down the magical giant toilet (I forget if they removed this or not). 

Buy coffee. 

Fly a giant blimp. And crash it.

Acquire high fashion. 

Ride a car down a mountain.

Terrorize the town on segways.

Roam the green wastelands in search of secrets.

And much, much, MUCH, more. 

Honestly more fun than I thought it'd be. There's fun clues to finding all sorts of secret stuff.

review:
Após a compra, você recebe 3 versões do mesmo jogo:
- Versão 1 ( a original e antiga ).
- Versão 2 (gráficos melhores, novas adições ao jogo).
- Versão 3 (em beta ainda, então recebe direto updates novos; apesar de ter seus problemas, essa é a melhor versão para se jogar).

Sinopse: Você controla um sapo com flatulências constantes, devido a algum problema gastrointestinal. Você anda por um território cercado pelo oceano, onde você pode obter roupas novas, mergulhar em peripécias, subir em outros anfíbios, morrer por tubarões ou assassinado por uma gangue, ir para o espaço, subir em um dirigível, ser atacado por formigas e outros animais gigantes, fugir de zumbis, encontrar um disco voador, explodir bombas, dirigir diversos automóveis diferentes, peidar e etc...

Recomendo.

review: After owning the game for years and playing through many updates, I can still say that I am finding new things in the game I never knew about when I play. Though all of the friends i play this with are usually busy, so I don't play too much anymore, but I love it when I do. It's a lot of fun just to mess around and play games. The new update is somewhat lacking in content at the moment but since the old version is still available, this isn't a big issue. I really look forward to seeing how this game develops and finding more dumb and silly things to do with my friends.

author: {'steamid': '76561198258799392', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 9, 'playtime_forever': 8465, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 8384, 'last_played': 1700530150}
review:
While its been about two years since I played this game, thinking about it still fills me with great joy.

This game is one of my favourites of all time, and I truly think it gives us some insight into the world of frogs.

Whether you're fighting [spoiler]giant sharks, giant worms, or giant ants[/spoiler] the game continues to be very comedic, while challenging and well designed. Not to mention the amount of content: in almost 140 hours I still haven't done everything.

Amazing Frog? taught me about the value of fart jokes and frog shenanigans, and how the lives of frogs can teach us about how terribly boring our own lives are. 

My only problem with this game is the raft time trial at Swindon on Sea because fuck that I tried it so many times while the sharks were here its so fucking hard oijhgftwerewhfrwrwrewr

author: {'steamid': '76561198051054561', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 6, 'playtime_forever': 58, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 58, 'last_played': 1637257730}
review:
Сын просил купить эту игру. Посмотрел трейлер и увидел "очень положительные" отзывы. 
1. Хоть графика очень убогая, игра весит очень много и плохо оптимизирована, подлагивает и подтормаживает (если ребята делают игру с такой примитивной графикой ,то можно было сделать это на нормальном движке)
2. Суть игры вообще непонятна, типа песочница, но по факту лягушка просто пердит и взаимодействие с окружающим миром минимально, да и еще она падает каждые 5 метров пути.
ВЫВОД: игра некачественная,как в техническом плане,так и в играбельном.Очень скучная. Такой продукт подойдет только для категории "бесплатно" но точно не за эти деньги которые требует продавец.

author: {'steamid': '76561198863148021', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 1, 'playtime_forever': 3924, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 1172, 'last_played': 1704258570}
review:
一，开局从小绿门出，看右手边的墙画，上面说的是在一栋有苍蝇标志的大楼上有一个绿色的中间画着枪的按钮。这个东西在你当前十一点钟方向（前方偏左）最角落的大楼上，通过邻近楼的弹簧床上去。踩按钮将解锁枪械mod，按esc使用手机，在手机里用方向键选择该枪械mod，使主世界（斯文登市）出现枪械刷新点。大部分刷的是炸弹不能炸僵尸，按R丢出去别炸自己。刷出的东西里，镭射枪伤害高但是不会在下水道出现（按鼠标右键据枪腰射），火箭筒不能杀僵尸而且没准心会炸自己，ak子弹多，双管猎枪喷僵尸好用，喷火器烤僵尸只能烧白骨而且僵尸能动，弩低伤少弹无用，手枪伤低弹少无用。
二，出了枪械就可以做很多事情了。先去探险下水道。下水道很多人说难。按w和shift加速跑，呱呱会跑得快，但是大概四秒就会倒，在倒之前，只要按着鼠标右键，会保持稳定（但是会慢），每次在倒之前点一下就行了。基本去拿门卡都没问题。方法二，下水道下方墙壁上有一台工程车，可以开进去跑图（不会被咬到），就是要小心被僵尸卡模型顶翻车和各种翻车到沟里。
三，拿了门卡就可以去101避难所了。避难所是个回廊，贴边走就不会漏东西。捡齐六个显微镜将打开红力场，可以进行飞船飞行，同时解锁了登月火箭（飞行许可按E在桌子上）。
四，解锁火箭后要加油，需要红色方形油箱。驾驶非工程车，撞车或黄色油桶概率获得。按手机上的出口键，最下面一个选项是回家、刷新主世界资源。登月的内容我没探索太多。镭射枪是在月球我才刷到的，月球有大沙虫攻击呱呱。
五，主世界。手机里的s.c.p是市民积分，攒到一半（700分）市中心门口（就是你出门、大炮指向的楼）会有平衡车，攒到1500分会在市中心墙上给个扳手，修理城门的电源。
六，攒分。抓小偷去市中心背面的警察局。用双管猎枪（好用）杀天上的鸽子，然后丢到咖啡厅旁边一个血淋淋的搅碎机。把地上的信丢邮箱，把地上的空瓶子丢垃圾桶。其他的不知道怎么做。
七，市外。沿着大门外的路向前开车，会到达海边，有马桶、公交车，打开枪械mod可以有一个刷枪装置。海里的鲨鱼可以杀，无限刷新，海边的其他呱呱可以丢给鲨鱼咬成骨头。
向右，在内陆湖边有个鳄鱼沙雕，带镭射枪去，在它旁边观察一下，按几下e，大鳄鱼会出来，小心，鳄鱼能秒你，而且速度很快，还有湖边有能秒你的小鳄鱼，镭射大概五枪死。
继续向右有片平原，没什么东西了，可以坐飞艇回来，C上升空格下降。

author: {'steamid': '76561198145898549', 'num_games_owned': 48, 'num_reviews': 2, 'playtime_forever': 21924, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 21749, 'last_played': 1653753626}
review:
This is his son- We have been playing amazing frog for like 4+ years now and it is such a fun game to play with your family and friends. There's guns, cars, spaceships, you can fly too the moon, become Darth Vader, fight off sharks, or even find a huge Megalodon deep out in the ocean. Wish the game got as much updates as it used too and my little brother play's this game still once every now and than. I will for sure recommend this for anyone looking to buy this game! But one thing I wish was in the game is for sure deep sea exploration hopefully this will be added to the game one day also with a submarine!!!
Edit- Just played the game for the first time in like a year no offense but this new update sucks they took everything out and I just wrote a good review

author: {'steamid': '76561198437467213', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 101, 'playtime_forever': 160, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 160, 'last_played': 1575609588}
review:
Nah. I can see what kind of audience would be into this. and maybe if I got a whole bunch of palls together to play then maybe... but... not like this. not on my own.

This game is weird. and in a way I have to respect it. I played multiple games and each time I found something new that defied expectation. and saying that makes me want to go back. but again, not on my own. This game is inviting you to explore and to break it. But if that doesn't sound fun to you, then I'd steer clear.

If you enjoyed games like goat simulator for similar reasons then by all means pick this one up. a messy and insane sandbox game with no clear motive is sometimes all we need. But some people want a game with some semblance of purpose other than random nonsense.

review: 今天发一个新手攻略，讲一下皮肤或成就的获得方法，绳索枪scp积分达到三百可以解锁，皮肤城里有很多个，城外也有几个，月球上的UFO有三个，下水道也有，scp积分可以通过杀僵尸，扔垃圾到垃圾桶，把信件放到信箱等。青蛙牛奶咖啡店的积分可以通过把箱子给破坏获得，要去月球先去下水道找到博士的尸体把门卡拿走，然后再拿门卡开门，开完门了进去房间寻找六个显微镜，放到对应的地方，红外线封住的地方就会打开，里面有火箭发射的允许，在去炸车获得汽油灌满火箭就可以去月球了，收集显微镜的地方还有个额外的彩蛋，就是其中有一个房间里面有一个管道，趴下来可以看到，钻进去可以到一个地方，里面有蚂蚁，让你救出六只青蛙，全部救完之后可以获得一个蚂蚁头套。气球背包，通过上月球去绿柱子解锁大沙虫，再去绿光旁边大沙虫碰到绿光死了就解锁喷气背包了，再去青蛙雕像的手上拿马桶塞，再返回月球的出生地点，放到火箭上，再回到气球背着喷气背包到大马桶里，就解锁气球背包了。以上内容如果你觉得有帮助的话就点个赞吧。

author: {'steamid': '76561198003232195', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 7, 'playtime_forever': 1868, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 1, 'playtime_at_review': 1557, 'last_played': 1711396919}
review:
The Amazing Frog:
This is a very funny game, It fits well for kids to. Brilliant map, can explore the beach and the ocean if you want to.
Crock's and Sharks are there to. Find a Megaladon and a giant version of the Crock's is well.

Land-Scape:
It's Massive, you can do and explore pretty much whatever you want really, can find a Reg Megaladon in the ocean if your lucky enough. Find a giant explosive tank on an island. This Land-Scape gets a 90/100.

Guns/Zombies:
There is a great big green button on the highest building in Swindon and once you hit it you unlock gun Spawn's and you can get a Sniper, Deagle, Shot-Gun, Frog Zapper, Rocket Launchers, Water Gun, Flame-thrower and a AK-47. Nice!
Zombies can be found in the sewers and there are a lot of them down there, if you take a weapon down there you will loose it, it doesn't spawn with you but there are some down there. They can get you if your not careful. This gets a 70/100.

Challenges:
You get all these crazy, weird and fun events. For all events any that you completed it could be like Finding presents, Getting hidden items. You will get a reward once you finished it. It may have a bonus feature added to it to. 67/100.

Moon and space.
This is by far probably the best thing in the game, because there is just so much to it. For the main event you have to find 5 Kittens and take them to there coloured rocket and send them back to Earth, but be careful though because you might run into SAND WORMS!! They are basically like Graboids from the movie 'Tremors' and they are speedy and hard to kill, and you could run into a big one to...The easiest way to kill the big one is find a hidden lazer and make it run into it, as of the small ones you could just use a rocket launcher and it would be over. 99/100.

The Magic Toilet:
You can find a tiny toilet with a poop inside near the back of Swindon and you can activate to become big when you have the Plunger in the Frog Statue on the moon and come back and interact with it, After you made it big. Any items you put inside will become big, if you have the Jet-Pack unlocked you can turn it into a Balloon one instead. Very funny! 90/100

Costumes:
There are a staggering amount in this game, some are even secret, it's a very fun and huge adventure to find them. You could find them on islands, buildings, on top of buildings sometimes in a hidden spot. You CAN EVEN GET STAR WARS! 77/100

This Game Is Very fun! I Don't play it much, for me i just like to explore instead of doing the tasks, i will do them at some point though, This game gets a 70/100.

review:
o jogo é mt bom, de vdd, pode parecer meio tosco mas é MT divertido, amo esse jogo, porem ele é MUITO mal otimizado, ainda mais na nova versão, ent se seu PC n é tão bom, n se engane pelos gráficos, ele parece ser leve só, mas n é

mas é muito divertido andar por aí, ir pra lua, lutar com minhocas gigantes, jogar coisas numa privada e deixa-las maiores, acabar com o megalodon, buscar roupinhas pelo mapa (q por sinal é bem grande mas meio vazio), uma coisa legal é q constantemente vc acaba ficando preso na parede, porem vc pode sair usando o app stuck no celular (do jogo), fora q é ótimo causar um apocalipse tubarão ou um apocalipse zumbi, de geral é um game 8,5/10, só n dou um 9 por causa da otimização msm, se os desenvolvedores tirassem um tempo pra otimizar bem o jogo ele ficaria show

a nova versão dele q é quase um remake é bem ruim ainda, é ainda mais mal otimizada e n tem nd pra fazer no mapa, fora q n tem as coisas mais características da versão normal

enfim, Sapo espetacular.

review:
*WARNING THIS IS A REVIEW FOR THE "LEGACY" OR V2 VERSION OF THE GAME*
I highly recommend this game to anyone looking for a casual silly game. The video potential for this game is incredible, but just playing the game and not recording it, since it has no multiplayer, can be a little boring... at first. This is because you eventually unlock things like the grapple hook and the key to the city, which allows for very easy exits to the outside world, which may look barren at first but there is a lot to see and do!

review:
V3 update. whew. This is a massively unfinished update, they should not have released this yet, i tried it, this isn't so much a update as it is a showcase, they took everything FUN out of the game, for me: There is no cars, sewer,  frogs, weapons, beach, sharks, etc. that is everything FUN about the game, all they really did, was update the graphics (Massively) and change a few things here and there,  this update is not fun, an any way, IMO its very bad honestly,  IF they released a more finished update, with the weapons, frogs, sewers, and Beach, this would be far more fun. It doesn't help that to me, this game is unplayable without the Jetpack, as you can't really run in the game, as you fall over to much, and its very annoying, so far, this update is very bad to me, i really hope they implement the actually fun stuff, soon.
For now i am sticking to LEGACY.

review: Comedy gold, physics silver, and overall PLATINUM! Amazing Frog is as amazing as it gets! a constantly expanding universe! perfectly-executed sounds! lots of secrets to uncover! If you want an In-your-face open world game, then this is not for you. BUT if you like it when people fart, or you're a fan of Grand Theft Auto, or you love weird and wonderful things, then feel free to download this game! It's fun! It's got rag-doll physics! It's only mildly psychotic! Join you friends on a high-quality time! a fayju-y time! you'll have a GRAND OLD TIME!!!

author: {'steamid': '76561198086745243', 'num_games_owned': 844, 'num_reviews': 92, 'playtime_forever': 43, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 43, 'last_played': 1607433943}
review:
Amazing Frog - это игра платформер про город, где вы управляете антропоморфной жабой.
Вам даётся большой город с кучей активностей, большинство основано на юморе. Вы можете прокатиться в машине, давить других жаб, пукать, носиться по городу, запускать себя из пушки и ещё много всего.
Это игра похожа по содержанию на Goat Simulator.
Игра мне НЕ понравилась, потому что она скучная. Чтобы что-то найти, надо долго ходить по городу, но большинство вещей не такие уж и смешные. Пробовал играть в эту игру пару раз и ничем она меня не притянула. В тоже время Goat Simulator зашёл "на ура".
Ещё не нравится, что жаба падает каждые несколько секунд. Можно встать, но все равно раздражает. Представьте, что в Симуляторе Козы Коза падала бы каждые несколько секунд.
Может быть вы скажете, что я недостаточно исследовал игру, но эта игра меня совершенно не затянула.

Игру не рекомендую.

author: {'steamid': '76561199065737911', 'num_games_owned': 56, 'num_reviews': 21, 'playtime_forever': 643, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 222, 'last_played': 1676745142}
review:
Sigh.... This game, This game..... This game is one of the most random games I have ever played in my life. There is so much to do, yet you have no idea what to do. There are so many easter eggs, from the "ti**ies" car, to the twerking alligators. It's better played on controller than mouse because the controls are a lot easier to learn. This game is amazing with friends, and pretty good by yourself. Only a bit of criticism. One, they need new updates, pretty sure they are working on v3 though. Two, don't make it splitscreen for multiplayer.

Overall score: 9/10

author: {'steamid': '76561199033821461', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 3, 'playtime_forever': 835, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 186, 'last_played': 1708229815}
review:
참신하고 재미있긴 한데 노트북으로 하니까 렉 많아서 한번 빡치고 조작감이 개떡같아서 한번 더 빡친다 특히 스킨 모으는 것도 참신하긴한데 조작키 모르는 어린이등 아니면 뉴비들은 얻고싶은 스킨은 그림에 떡같은 존제다 그리고 특히 (스포주의)우주가기 전에 지하에서 좀비나오는데 길 모르면 뼈다귀 카드 찾는다고 1시간은 기본으로 날라간다 우주에선 특히 자이언트 우주괴물 잡는데 그 괴물이 광선에 않맞아서 진짜 빡치기도 한다 그리고 변기 얻으려면 
우주에있는 손바닥에 올라서서 뚜러뻥가지고 우주선에 넣어야하는데 조작감 개떡같아서 일반 우주괴물한테 
잡아먹히고 그리고 지하에 있는 현미경찾는데 조작 모르면 3시간 각이 나온다
(친구에게 추천해서 오열하는걸 보며 쾌감을 느끼는걸 좋아하는사람에게 추천한다)

review:
이게임은 안돼는것도 많고 힘든게많다는게 콤플렉스인 게임이다.
이때 개구리는 떠올랐다
악세사리는 커녕 코슈튬도 얻기힘들다는걸 깨달았다....
하지만 갓겜이라서 안할순없다 개인적으로 스팀게임중에 가장 재밌던 게임이다 DLC도 추가됬으면 좋겠다!
하지만
이때 또 개구리는 떠올랐다......
다음 업데이트가 11월에 된다는것을.....
어메이징프로그.....
적어도 1달에 한번씩은 업데이트하지....
'어메이징프로그는 업데이트를 너무 안한다
하지만 재밌는게 콤플랙스다 그런데....
11월에 업데이트된다는건 사실이다
어메이징 프로그 1년 넘게 업데이트를 하지않은적도있다
업데이트는 너무 안한다 그래도 업데이트를 Aㅏ주 ㄱr끔 하는 만큼  그만큼 사람들이 만족할 업데이트를 하지않을까?
물론 염소시뮬레이터게임도 업데이트 john na 안한다
나는 업데이트하기전에 모든코슈툼을 얻어보고싶다....

author: {'steamid': '76561198861897964', 'num_games_owned': 34, 'num_reviews': 1, 'playtime_forever': 783, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 187, 'last_played': 1692590605}
review: This game is amazing (frog?) but it still has its down sides. If you have a low end PC or laptop like mine, you wont be able to roam around Swindon as you wish, well you can, but you will have at the most 1 to 2 fps, and walk backwards. But there are also test servers for different game modes which run at 18 to 25 fps for me,    my favourite test server is the zombie sewer one, you're in a sewer filled with zombies and you can run from them and even kill them with the weapons scattered around. There is also more test rooms, (3 more, 4 in total).  One of the alternate test rooms is a multiplayer call of duty type building fight room, where you pickup weapons from around the building with vending machines which give out unlimited ammo, though there is no online multiplayer, so you will need a controller for 2 player split screen. I highly recommend this game. Online multiplayer will be coming very soon.

author: {'steamid': '76561198031397568', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 1, 'playtime_forever': 41065, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 29669, 'last_played': 1710381966}
review:
My son found this game for us to play together.  I was at first, a bit put off.  The graphics feel very old.  The frog keeps falling whenever you run over a curb.  You are a bipedal frog.  Nothing makes sense!

But wow, my first impression was wrong.  This game has many layers.  It's fun exploring, finding new things, uncovering new places.  My son and I have had many laugh-filled evenings playing together.  

We highly recommend this game.

author: {'steamid': '76561198322460611', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 3, 'playtime_forever': 1212, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 1212, 'last_played': 1592610964}
review:
Amazing Frog

Contras:

-Bugs de mais! Porém fica bom com amigos
-Fps Baixo na cidade
-Abandonaram o jogo

Prós

-Super divertido com amigos
-Nós nem ligamos para bugs quando jogamos com amigos
-MUITA coisa para fazer
-É garantida horas de diversão mesmo sozinho porém com amigos é bem melhor

review:
Getting sub-30 frames on "Great" with a Ryzen 3600 CPU, a Radeon 5600 XT and 32GB of RAM.

I took a peek in my hardware monitor and none of them were being utilized (graphics card sat around 10 percent, CPU sat around 5 percent) 

I would suspect that for some reason it's running off of integrated graphics somehow but my CPU doesn't even have integrated graphics.

I'm not going to refund because I believe in the game, but this is a stressful bug.

review: This game is very fun and truly endless. This game is extremely enjoyable with friends, the co-op aspect of the game is what makes it fun, escaping the city is just the start, when you discover vehicles, guns, drones and grapples it becomes truly fun and endless. one of my favorite activities was racing with friends and messing with the physics with the grapple, this game is just cause but its only you, your friends and some farting npcs, you can complete quests like clean the streets or catch thieves, if you do enough of these you will be able to open the city's doors without having to climb the wall (in the new updates its become incredibly easy to climb the wall with the addition of grapples). Overall this game is an extremely fun with friends and alone, this review didnt contain any spoilers but there is things to do story wise, there is several quests, but you will have to find out what they are yourself! Did I forget to mention zombies?

review: eu comecei a jogar amazing frog em 2019 ou 2020, era tudo novo para mim eu não sabia de nada então ficava cambaleando por ai metendo tiro em sapo. esse jogo mudou a minha para sempre por isso agora eu só me comunico com RIBBIT, mas aqui esta tudo traduzido para você entender o que eu estou falando. enfim esse jogo alem de ter a essência de mundo aberto e muita, muita, muita e muita coisa pra pegar, que eu gosto, que você demora 50 anos da sua vida só pra fazer o 100% maaaaaaas ele tem um diferencial: SAPOS, PEIDOS, PRIVADAS, DESENTUPIDORES e essas coisas. agradeço a fayju por esse jogo maravilhoso de bonito e espero que as próximas gerações sintam o mesmo que eu senti: felicidade por matar sapos, raiva por morrer no blood world faltando umas 10 aboboras no hard mode e alivio por pegar a roupa do diabo

review: I cannot recommend this game as even on high-end PCs it runs terribly. The situation is that it is very badly optimised and it will run differently in a variety of computers. It might run as smooth as babies skin on a work PC but run horribly on a high-end gaming PC. I was looking forward to playing this game, but it is impossible with the frames I'm getting (10-30).

author: {'steamid': '76561198993576983', 'num_games_owned': 26, 'num_reviews': 12, 'playtime_forever': 541, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 204, 'last_played': 1691663365}
review:
My name is Walter Hartwell White. I live at 308 Negra Arroyo Lane, Albuquerque, New Mexico, 87104. This is my confession. If you're watching this tape, I'm probably dead, murdered by my brother-in-law Hank Schrader. Hank has been building a meth empire for over a year now and using me as his chemist. Shortly after my 50th birthday, Hank came to me with a rather, shocking proposition. He asked that I use my chemistry knowledge to cook methamphetamine, which he would then sell using his connections in the drug world. Connections that he made through his career with the DEA. I was... astounded, I... I always thought that Hank was a very moral man and I was... thrown, confused, but I was also particularly vulnerable at the time, something he knew and took advantage of. I was reeling from a cancer diagnosis that was poised to bankrupt my family. Hank took me on a ride along, and showed me just how much money even a small meth operation could make. And I was weak. I didn't want my family to go into financial ruin so I agreed. Every day, I think back at that moment with regret. I quickly realized that I was in way over my head, and Hank had a partner, a man named Gustavo Fring, a businessman. Hank essentially sold me into servitude to this man, and when I tried to quit, Fring threatened my family. I didn't know where to turn.
Eventually, Hank and Fring had a falling out. From what I can gather, Hank was always pushing for a greater share of the business, to which Fring flatly refused to give him, and things escalated. Fring was able to arrange, uh I guess I guess you call it a "hit" on my brother-in-law, and failed, but Hank was seriously injured, and I wound up paying his medical bills which amounted to a little over $177,000. Upon recovery, Hank was bent on revenge, working with a man named Hector Salamanca, he plotted to kill Fring, and did so. In fact, the bomb that he used was built by me, and he gave me no option in it. I have often contemplated suicide, but I'm a coward. I wanted to go to the police, but I was frightened. Hank had risen in the ranks to become the head of the Albuquerque DEA, and about that time, to keep me in line, he took my children from me. For 3 months he kept them. My wife, who up until that point, had no idea of my criminal activities, was horrified to learn what I had done, why Hank had taken our children. We were scared. I was in Hell, I hated myself for what I had brought upon my family. Recently, I tried once again to quit, to end this nightmare, and in response, he gave me this. I can't take this anymore. I live in fear every day that Hank will kill me, or worse, hurt my family. I... All I could think to do was to make this video in hope that the world will finally see this man, for what he really is

author: {'steamid': '76561198000189253', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 1, 'playtime_forever': 8353, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 3910, 'last_played': 1676262059}
review:
We (my housemates and I) have played this game since it was on the OUYA, and missed it so much that we bought it on PC.

The Amazing Frog is a game about messing around, persistence, and discovery. If you wanted to go all literary-analysis on it, you could say that the ease with which you fall down and get back up again plays into the theme of persistence. But honestly I think the devs just thought it was funny.

The main gameplay loop is something like this. Mess around until you find something weird and new to interact with. Try lots of things with it until it unlocks something. With the new unlocks, rinse and repeat. This loop wasn't really present in the OUYA version, and I think it's an overall improvement that lengthens the appeal of the game and gives it an occasional magical quality. Don't be expecting *amazing* discoveries though; we're talking small stuff here. This game works best with no explanation and little to no expectations. It is exactly as dumb as it looks, with lots of fart humor and the occasional pop culture or current events reference. I think the unabashed silliness of it goes so dumb that it wraps back around to funny for us.

This game is great for all ages and skill levels. Finding everything can involve some tricky platforming and/or some problem-solving, and getting good with the controls takes some work as they are a bit awkward. But I think the slapstick nature of the game where you're falling down all over the place, plus the way that the game lets you do everything at your own pace, helps folks not take their mistakes or struggles with the game too seriously. I put gamers and non-gaming folks in front of this game and all manage to have a great time, even playing simultaneously.

There are some things i miss about the OUYA version; mainly the numerous ways in which many mechanics completely subverted your expectations (eg. cannons, jumping, [spoiler]zombies[/spoiler] only being able to knock you down). We also really miss Party mode, as it was a riot (although I'm glad to see the falling-forever map go, cool as it was). That said, if you are a fan of GTA-esque sandboxes or "unfolding" games, this is a good one to try!

author: {'steamid': '76561198375000355', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 12, 'playtime_forever': 1162, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 800, 'last_played': 1641763026}
review:
Wow. This game is... a game. That I like.
It takes some special skills to laugh at this game over and over again.
And I have those skills.
Anyways, what I'm trying to say is that I really like this game! Looking at it, you might think "this is just some dumb game with a frog that has poor motor skills and eats taco bell at least seven times a day" which... is half correct. Take that as you will. But this game can be sooo much more than that, if you let it! You can be a police frog, grabbing criminals and locking them up (and when I say grabbing, I MEAN grabbing. You just grip 'em by the noggin and...yea). Or you can travel to space, after you get gas for the rocket by repeatedly jumping on cars until they explode and spew out fuel. I wish I was joking. Rescue cats, kill zombies, go to the gym and unleash a giant shark in the pool by pressing that big red button. There are so many things this game has to offer, it'll keep you entertained for hours. Sure, there's bugs, but every game has it's glitches. Mostly it's just your frog getting stuck that's an issue, but there's a specific app in the phone to help with that, which is neat!
So yes. Buy the game. Do it. Now. DO IT RIGHT NOW!

I've loved this game since 2014, or was it 2013?

Amazing Frog? is a bizarre (and even slightly frightening) dream you can enjoy with your friends.

review:
THIS GAME IS ABSOLUTELY EXCELLENT!!!!! But, I have a few bugs to report.
1. When I have the 'Ultron' quality setting on, my frog sometimes runs, even walks, backwards! 
2. I don't know why this happens but when I sometimes run or walk with trash or anything in my hand, it drops! It is really annoying.
3. My screen is constantly flashing when I play, even when I am in the ALL the LOADING SCREENS! Someone else made a comment about this one in the 'Bugs' Steam Community. 
Anyway, I hope you read all this, Fayju, and keep up the excellent work!!!!

review:
Ahh, i remember watching people play this game like few years ago and decided to buy it, it is fun and has A LOT of easter eggs and places to go. It is a open sandbox game with quirky machanics.
However this games controls are really bad, the sensitivity is FUBAR and in the new update the control of the plane is impossible.
The game doesnt run that well, the devs need to work on optimising the game and fixing that sensitivity.
I would aso want online multiplayer as this game lacks that a lot and its kinda bouring to play by yourself

review:
Lets Go Over The PROS And CONS

PROS:
Adding Online Multiplayer
Funny Gameplay
Sandbox
Based On A Real Place (London)
HUMONGOUS Map!

CONS:
No Cheats (Would Really Like It If You Were To Add Noclip)
Hard Controls
Stuck As Playing As A Ragdoll (You Flop EVERYWHERE)
When Out Of City, Hard To Find "Outside" Places.

SUMMARY:
I Totally Give This Game A SOLID 9/10, Only Because Of No Cheat Thingys Like Noclip, Which WOULD Be REALLY Useful!

review:
The game is coming along now and the developers seem to be getting to know the new upgraded engine well which has seen the frog fart hop,better driving physics come back along with better performance and graphics.

Some things from the legacy version are still missing, such as the grapple hook and sharks, so hopefully they can make a comeback, but we are starting to see more regular new stuff being added which is exciting to see.

I would like to see some form of wildlife added to forest parts just to liven the world up a bit more.

Anyway I have changed my rating back to positive.

author: {'steamid': '76561198000440135', 'num_games_owned': 439, 'num_reviews': 7, 'playtime_forever': 562, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 562, 'last_played': 1493643403}
review:
***Approximately how long will this game be in Early Access?***
“We are aiming to take it out of Early Access next year, there are currently so many ways to play Amazing Frog? But we want more Swindon, more vehicles, more challenges, more physics chaos. It will be hard to know when to stop and move to full release and even then we will not stop having plans for expanding the Amazing Frog Universe!”


I'm pretty sure this EA thing has been here since 2017. Not having any dates on something you use as a time-frame is kinda shady. Hasn't updated with anything worthwhile in probably a year. All anyone wants is to play this with friends, and the developers have said they'll do it, but instead they've pushed minor features.

The game itself is fun for maybe two or three hours on your own, maybe a day or two with local friends to play with, but it's basically a Goat Simulator style game. You'll play it for maybe an hour, get bored, then stop playing. You might play it again when they add some minor content. It's banked a lot of their hopes off of the Game Grumps video, too? Which just feels... weird. Especially considering the version they played was the OUYA copy (and we all know how the OUYA went, which... might be telling of how this game will go.) I don't have problems with recommending the game itself, if silly physics with friends on your couch is something your after, but I have big problems with developers promising things then ghosting their playerbase. I'd be willing to change my review if... any of the larger features they've spoken about came through.

review: Amazing Frog? é um jogo de Sandbox Sensacional. A quantidade de coisas para fazer é ENORME, desde ir até a Lua, até caçar Megalodons. Os gráficos são ótimos, e rodam na maioria dos computadores (menos em um dos meus, modelo 2008 q tá ferrado, e deu tela azul). Tem uma variedade muito vasta de personagens e armas, além da placa dos carros terem nomes de alguns Youtubers. O preço é realmente razoável por um jogo desse tipo, recomendo demais.

review:
Controls aren't the best and the Frogs fall like lead balloons but my goodness it's enjoyable playing local co-op. 
Single player can get dull and the map feels empty. Not a huge issue though, not when having too much fun falling over each other's player either stumbling into a car or trying to dodge shark-possessed pedestrians. 
The map isn't limited to the town of Swindon and it's got its simple charms of a world that will hopefully be built upon.

Amazing frog est franchement comparable à Goat simulator.

Vous incarnez une grenouille, et vous vous baladez dans un monde ouvert plus ou moins sans but si ce n'est la découverte et faire du grand n'importe quoi par pur plaisir.

author: {'steamid': '76561198080692382', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 113, 'playtime_forever': 117, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 117, 'last_played': 1552656838}
review:
(Gonna try and keep this short as Steam seems to be refusing my extra-long review, which was filled with feedback)

Amazing Frog is a weird game, and I don't mean that in a good way. I decided to get it for two reasons: the first is that the premise seems similar to Goat Simulator's and I love playing that game whenever I'm down. The second is that the community claims the game has loads of content, which I'm inclined to believe given it's been in early access for nearly five (!!!) years.

I usually have a list of pros and cons on my reviews but since I failed to find anything that pleases me, I'll just point out what I didnt like. 

- The world is huge, which wasn't necessary at all. Makes it feel awfully empty. Many times, less is more.
- NPC routines are too random, with barely any script (not talking about the code, but what they do "narratively"). It makes the world feel even more empty when you consider Goat Simulator NPCs were placed organically around maps, with some of them serving specific purposes such as filling out lines, protesting, or posing as policemen, to name a few. They added flavor to each maps, even offering some degree of narrative.
- Although the community claims there's a lot of content and the YouTube videos I saw demonstrate some of that, the layout of the map and gameplay design are too unintuitive to make discovering features satisfying at all. Even when I found something (the sewers in my case), it felt underwhelming and barely put together to pose as content. 
- Navigating the starting city is a bit of a nuisance and the overall map is even worse due to how empty it is, with a few things seemingly spread out as though this was just a testing level instead of a fully playable one.

There are a lot of signs and markers on the map which suggest the city will be remodeled somewhat and additional towns will be added in future updates, but considering how the game is after almost five years of early access, I just fail to see how it'll change in a meaningful way. It feels like an oddly designed tech demo and the ideas it proposes, while exciting on paper, don't manifest well at all.

If you want a silly open world game where you don't have to think much about what to do, just get Goat Simulator (though it isn't as open world as this intends to be, each map is its own open-ended experience). Although it's quite a broken game in many ways and some parts of it don't make much sense at all, it's a thought-out experience with a lot of attention to detail.

I enjoyed this game more than i thought i would when i got it because the gameplay is just amazing and i really enjoy the style of the characters and the map.
Some of my favourite things about it are the unlockable costumes and areas of the map and all of the secrets/easter eggs of content creators that have made videos on this game.
I would highly recommend to anyone that likes a open world game with a ton of secrets to find.
This game also has an amazing multiplayer feature which just makes the game play more fun for when your not unlocking the secrets.

author: {'steamid': '76561198331713076', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 3, 'playtime_forever': 3999, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 3130, 'last_played': 1662230362}
review:
このゲームを買う人は1つ注意しておくことがあります。
それはかなりアップデートが遅い事です。アーリーアクセスとしてSteamに並んでますが年に2回ほどしかアプデが来ません。
ただ、毎回アプデが来る度にかなり面白い要素が追加されます！
このゲームはこれと言ってすることはありませんが、楽しもうと思えばいくらでも楽しめます！
車でドリフトしながら街を駆け抜けたり、飛行船を操縦して壁の外を冒険したり、グラップリングフックでジャス〇コーズのように飛び回ったり、サメと戯れたり(即死)他にも巨大アリを退治したりと、遊びの巣窟です！
ぜひ、価格も安いですし買ってみてはどうでしょうか！

review: 《膜力蛤》是一款不仅要钱买，而且要命玩的暴力游戏。画风就同类型的游戏来说差了点，而且对于新手很不友好（主要是那些too young too simple的新手不知道怎么赚钱和出城，又naive到不喜欢翻攻略，比如刚入坑的我）。但不得不说这是一款很不错的游戏，可以说整个游戏就是让你找彩蛋，多人游戏时大家一起互助，同时你又得时刻盯紧你的朋友防止他拿水枪把你射♂动弹不得。真的相当exciting

author: {'steamid': '76561198027188122', 'num_games_owned': 482, 'num_reviews': 52, 'playtime_forever': 7252, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 3268, 'last_played': 1695082751}
review:
My son begged me to get this after he saw some channel on YouTube called "Fgteev" play it. I caved, and bought it. 
I personally have played around 20 hours or so of it, the rest was/is my kids. 

The game is a wacky open world sandbox where you play as a frog who has a terrible time standing up. There's surprisingly a ton of things to do and find in the game, and I enjoyed ever hour I put into it. So if you're planning on buying this just for yourself, watch a couple gameplay videos first. If you have kids, don't even bother with the videos -- just buy the game.

author: {'steamid': '76561198185282501', 'num_games_owned': 531, 'num_reviews': 5, 'playtime_forever': 5941, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 5886, 'last_played': 1643575241}
review: This is the best open world game to ever exist and I don't think anything else has a chance of toppling this masterpiece. This isn’t a mere game, it is an artistic statement about society and frogs. This game has had a deep impact on me since I was able to draw parallels between this game and my real life like how I’ve always wanted to be a frog ever since I was 7 years old. This is the quintessential open world shooter game with tons of secrets and hidden items meaning so a completionist can get a ton of time out of this masterwork of game design. This game has incredible graphical techniques such as the use of ray tracing and 12x anti-aliasing which has never been seen before in a video game especially not one of this caliber. In this game, you play as a frog and all you have to do is explore. The map is 14 square kilometers in size and is jam-packed with secret costumes and weapons. This was the first game to ever accurately recreate the surface of the moon in a game setting down to the placement of the rocks. The game has amazing movement that looks realistic and plays well unlike rockstar’s recent efforts with realistic movement which ended up being clunky and annoying to maneuver around. This game was also one of the first games to ever incorporate cooperative play simultaneously with up to 4 players all at once with the breakthrough technology of split screen along with accurate ragdolls and a perfectly recreated version of the city Swindon. I cannot recommend this game enough and I honestly believe there are no bad aspects of this game. This game is what devs should strive to create because no other game has been able to reach the same level of quality that this title has and I doubt at this point that it will ever be reached.

author: {'steamid': '76561198375906668', 'num_games_owned': 286, 'num_reviews': 7, 'playtime_forever': 3469, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 3469, 'last_played': 1660771788}
review:
One word: amazing. Amazing Frog? is clearly Fayju's magnus opus, a work of art who's sheer brilliance shines through each and every moment in the game. The gameplay is, for lack of a better word; jaw-dropping. The euphoria you will get by experiencing it for yourself is unlike anything you will ever experience. Inspired by other far inferior sandbox games such as Grand Theft Auto, it not only improves on, but dances on the terrible, horrifying gameplay that the series is used to. First time players of the game may notice that it is a bit floaty. However, this is actually one of the games biggest draws, allowing for you to make much greater jumps than in other sandboxes.

   The story, inspired by games such as Final Fantasy VII, is a work of art within itself, requiring many days to fully decrypt it's meaning, akin to a modern enigma code. Once again, the developers' sheer brilliance is seen through the subtle details in the environment, which although simple at first, contain massive clues at the storytelling dripping out of it's every pore. Of course, I won't spoil it here, for you to discover it yourself. However, sub-125 IQ simpletons will likely not be able to grasp it's true meaning.

   Clearly, fans of other sandbox games such as Garry's Mod and S&Box are nothing but mindless sheep, pretending to enjoy the slop that is given to them day-by-day. It is only us, the Amazing Frog? fans, who can become immune to their propaganda and see that those games are nothing but mindless drivel, sheer dumpster-fires of technical short-sightedness hidden behind a wafer thin premise.

Trieste-Zurich-Paris
1914-1921

Ribbit.

review:
It's like goat sim, but with a good art style, and fun, and well, the list goes on.

Edit: Oh yeah, this game is on the OUYA. In game, there is a mechanic where you can pick up trash and throw it away. I found and OUYA, and said "Wait a minute", I think you know what I did next. Nobody has ever TRASHED on the OUYA that hard. Thank you developers.

Yet another, not edit more, addition to my review: Ok, this is made by 2 people. It's optimized very well for 2 people, and it feels like PEOPLE made it, not a company. There are references to different games and shows and it's feels cool when you're like "Ayy, I get that joke". I really love this game, 2 is also my lucky number, so that just makes it even more special to me.

Edit: I got banned from the discussions because I made a joke, and put in suggestions for fun/ to make it funnier. And I got banned. The rules say the post shall be removed, so what the hell moderators.

review: It's Grand Theft Auto as a frog.  This is how kids can fly under the radar, and still play GTA without getting in trouble with their mom.  It has identical mechanics.  Steal a car, punch a cop, play Donald Trump, jump in a blimp, and fly up into the clouds.  It has great split screen. My kids love it.  So much depth to a stupid frog game. There are even frog zombies, sharks that chase you while you ride a jet ski.  And look out for the mega shark.  This game is sweet.

review: This is going to be a short review, all I have to say is that this game NEEDS online multiplayer, I will happily purchase this game for all my friends if it can be pulled off. Otherwise, this is a great game with tons of potential, hopefully we can get online compatibility upon full release. If you're looking for a multiplayer experience, then you're going to have to settle for local multiplayer for now. However this game is plenty fun when played solo, if you can find fun by yourself easily, you'll find yourself putting a lot of time into this title. Here's to hoping for a full release soon to a game i've been following for 2 years now.

author: {'steamid': '76561197999252895', 'num_games_owned': 80, 'num_reviews': 17, 'playtime_forever': 1747, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 15, 'last_played': 1577961482}
review:
Игра не заслужено имеет такое маленькое Российское коммьюнити. 
Честно говоря я с друзьями тоже не сразу восприняли игру в серьез (просто скачали на каком то левом сайте),
но когда мы осознали что эта игра больше чем просто угар на часик нам открылся невероятный мир Эмейза.
Купил игру так как захотел поддержать разраба и первым поиграть в грандиозное обновление названное V3!
О игре:
Amazing frog? Это когда:
-Лягушка служила в десанте и может преземлятся без парашюта.
-Пасхалок в игре больше чем самой игры.

review: My daughter (7 years old) loves this game. On my own, I would probably have played it for 20 minutes, figured that it's meaningless and dropped out. However, with a 7-year old it has nearly unending potential for random shenaningans. The wobbly fart-boosted physics are strangely stimulating and maybe the best part of the game (although also very frustrating at times). The updates are a little slow, but usually add enough to keep us going for another hour or two. Amazing Frog? 2 is probably our most anticipated game.

review:

author: {'steamid': '76561198029464959', 'num_games_owned': 336, 'num_reviews': 57, 'playtime_forever': 844, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 825, 'last_played': 1579345147}
review:
You can play as a frog in a sandbox world, there is so much to do in this game you'll never find everything.

This is one of those games that you don't play to complete, you play it because you want to mess around and have a laugh.

Pros

- Lots of things to do, I mean LOTS
- The game is being actively updated by the developers
- Great fun alone or even more fun with friends
- Controller support, makes couch co-op even easier to do

Cons

- Performance is meh, it can make my 1060 struggle
- The thought of not being able to find everything can put some people off of the game.

Conclusion

Very fun game that you should definitely buy, but you may need a bit of a beefy PC.

review: Games like this can be fun for a few hours, but there really isnt anything to do once you get a few hours into it. I will admit, this game was very fun when I started, but I dont feel the same way anymore. 9/10 at the begining. 5/10 a few hours into it. I am not going to give it a no for just that though. Not only was it boreing a few hours into it, but the controls made me angry. I was expecting the spacebar to be JUMP, but It actually makes you fart. I would recommend this to anyone who always has a little free time. It can be fun, but you should probably not play it for countless hours. I just wanna thank the makers of this game, although it was not the right game for me, its probably the best game in the world for somebody else out there.

review: On the verge of playing 100 hours in Amazing Frog? i feel now prepared to write an adaquate review. First i want to thank the devs Gaz and Hal. I love these guys! they release regular dev blogs detailing what they are up to and they make some really good youtube videos. I dont really know what it is about this game that makes me come back time after time. Honestly its a little frightening at times. cause im a twenty year old guy who is playing a game about floppy frogs. whenever i tell my friends just that they look at me strange. but when we get on the game and start playing together its non-stop fun.      I cannot recommend this game enough! keep up the great work Fayju!!

review: My 5 year old loves this game. Farts, zombies, pigs, blimps, sharks, outter space? The Amazing Frog is a sandbox game that you can make your own fun in. Once you get the hang of bouncing off the trampolines and picking yourself up off the floor you'll find a fun world that you keep coming back to. The game just keeps getting better with every update. Highly recommend for the casual gamer and for kids!

author: {'steamid': '76561198276402748', 'num_games_owned': 77, 'num_reviews': 11, 'playtime_forever': 2274, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 466, 'last_played': 1547851777}
review: Not very good. felt myself constantly annoyed. its terrible falling feturemakes it almost as hard for a frog to cross the street as frogger. enemies are boring. tries to have a gta feel, but nothing has consequence. It should be an option to turn on cops or something. Guns were lame and pretty uneffective. it is a work in progress, but until this work makes progress, im saying i wouldnt recomend. Ill give them a fair cahnce. heres what i want to see. First, a falling feture is a good idea, but it to sensitive. Make it harder to fall. Second, i can shoot a zombie in the head 4 times with a sniper and not kill it. makes most guns useless. third, add cops that arent retarded. if they see me commiting mass murder, they should pull out guns and fire at me. it should be a toggle option for fans who like it this way. more fun to use wepons. if they add melee (or more melle if it already exist), that would be cool. Not asking for them to start from scratch, but if you toggle fall sensibillit, gun power, cops, and add a little more, this might be worth my 15 dollars and 99 cents.

review:
相当有毒的一款小游戏……主角没有任何目的和任务，但能让玩家玩得下去。

游戏内隐藏着各种梗，需要经过一段时间才能自己开发出来。
风格很卡通，而且很幽默，可以说是青蛙版GTA了。
支持本地分屏游玩——还是4P，厉害了我的蛙！

消磨时光的不错选择。
