author: {'steamid': '76561197963588013', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 208, 'playtime_forever': 1249, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 702, 'last_played': 1692523357}
review:
2023
Its still such a fun local co-op game so I must recommend it. I was so extremly dissapointed witht he promise of the Multiplayer support that was going to be released in 2017.

The regular Amazing Frog? is very good but the other one in developement is extremly laggy.. but still its quite much fun to goof around in as it is...the first one that is :)
------
Update 2019: Multiplayer was supposed to be released in 2017 as the devs wrote and promised that...BUT ...its a twoman team and of course stuff takes longer time. They said it would be ported over to a new engine, this was also talked about in 2017, nothing has happened with that either...NO NEW gamengine or mp...nothing except a few new things on the map.

I dont think the game is dead, but its extremly slow and the devs are not to be trusted about releasing it hehe...I mean multiplayer was supposed to be released at the end of 2017, perhaps 2019 december ?  I cant recommend it even if I would like too since the developers promise something but dont care to fullfill it.  


Update 2018: Not much at all has happened, the devs talked about that the online mode would be released 2017 but it was´nt and still late 2018 it has not come, there are  lots of talk and talk about stuff that is going on with the developement but to cut it short, allmost nothing has been added to the game since I bought it. Some RC cars you can drive and a swimmingpool and a gym but they have very limited funfactor to them. 

 So wait this game out intil they post the multiplayer feature or buy it cheap on a sale. It´s fun in local play to just run around and do pointless stuff, but still it heavily lacks of things to do.

"a 20Km Landscape" <- its written on the steamstore page, this is not true or at least not open to play ingame, perhaps there is a way to unlock it or it has been available in a previous version of the game. 12 of the screenshots on steamstore page are from places I never encountered while ingame with my friends, We played it together for 11 hours but never found any of these areas. The info about the game calls it hardcore parkour which couldnt be far from truth since you cant climb onto areas, usually you fall on yourself and fart at the same time...quite fun..but to call this game hardcore parkour is 100% incorrect, The  only thing you can climb ontop is another frog sit on that frogs shoulders, I wouldnt call that parkour haha.

And the above statement comes from a person  like me who really love Amazing frog?, but it´s its super dissapointing that nothing ever happens. But perhaps in 2020 we will get the online update or the promised move to a new unity engine, who knows :D

--Review 2016---
+ Neat and cozy local 4player splitscreen
+ Cute graphics 
+ Nice sandbox to play around in.


- Aggressive moderators that bans for their own
  odd reasons in the forums.    

- not much content but I´m sure it will be here 
   at the end of 2017 (hopefully)

review:
[h1]Amazing Frog? - Review[/h1]

'Amazing Frog?' is an open world sandbox, you play as a superhero frog who lives in a town called 'Swindon'. This game is hilarious singeplayer or with a friend(s), you can unlock a variety of costumes for your frog character by exploring the world around you, hidden up high or down low.

[h1]The Good[/h1]

• Lots Of Exploration

• Secrets Everywhere

• Funny References

• Plenty Of Vehicles

• Iconic Costumes

[h1]The Bad[/h1]

• Difficult Controls

• Occasionally Crashes

• Low Quality Graphics

[h1]Conclusion[/h1]

Amazing Frog is a lot of fun, it's weird and wacky contents and strange areas to explore make the game definitely worth buying. If you're seeking a silly game that you can play with friends up to 4, this game is definitely for you. Or if you're looking for a game that you can get a gun and shoot other frogs while riding a pig, this game is also for you.

review:
I really didnt know what to expect.  Having played such gems as goat simulator in the past I was expecting strange and this certainly delivers.

Run into town, throw a roll of toilet paper at a cop.  Steal a bus and try to jump train cars, land bus on top of first train car.  Grab a frog by the face and choke slam them to the concrete.  Shoot myself out of a cannon.  Walk into a portapotty and end up in a tardis thats actually inside of a toilet.  Go to the gym, get tripped by a break dancing frog.  Hit a giant red button by the gym pool and a shark appears in the pool.  Push a frog into the pool, shark eats the frog.

Yeah I'd recommend this HAHAHA WTF

Edit:  Oh and the farting.  Lots of farting.  and fart jokes.

author: {'steamid': '76561198071141082', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 46, 'playtime_forever': 4095, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 1893, 'last_played': 1707551958}
review:
This is like GTA with frogs, but you can interact with the world way more and it also has a huge aspect of those egglike exploration games.

Once you get used to the controls and your frog falling over (which really is just infuriating the first ten minutes into the game) you'll learn to appreciate progress way more and you'll probably have legit fun. Especially when playing this with friends it's a diamond made from shit.
I managed to get everyone I know to play this game, and that's rare.
In this game you can go exploring a huge world, that's always larger than it currently seems, with creative developers who are just as messed in the head as the people who buy this game and such always know where to place a good secret and where to hide a new mechanic or a new plaything for us.
And don't mind the early access, it might seem like "another one of these" games, but as far as I remember I had this game for more than a year now and the updates are still rolling in like they should, and the dev team has actually been working to port this game from unity 4 to unity 5 in it's entirety so they can add more complex and aesthatically pleasing content. No dev is a saint but at least the frog-game devs are mentally challenged.

Also be ware of sharks, they are by far the greatest enemy of frogkind in all aspects.

EDIT 2022: The developers are now developing... 2-3 completely different, separate versions of this game at the same time. One of them with graphics that go so hard even my high end gaming PC likes them. Expect yearly content updates that actually add quite a bit. I'll be real with you, I think these developers are insane but I also really like their way of doing things.

author: {'steamid': '76561198008489191', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 15, 'playtime_forever': 8547, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 627, 'last_played': 1652150089}
review:
Parts of this game are fun, especially for kids. If it gets completed it should be an awesome open world game.  But right now this game is nowhere near done. The ragdoll controls need work, just about everything seems to knock the frog over and several button presses are needed to get him back up again. Sometimes the frog gets stuck or weapons don't mesh right with the graphics. Some of the levels are very sparse and clearly unfinished. The game crashes, a lot. Sometimes on exit the game goes into an infinite loop.

This will be a good game, but I can't recommend it until the devs improve the controls and clipping problems.

review:
蛤长者，笑习习，
提着高腰裤，戴着黑框镜；
红衣秤砣续大命啊，
一续就是俩星期！

什么渠道干预，什么见风是雨，
什么无中生有，什么中央钦定；
什么报导偏差，什么西方道理；
要论姿势水平，不知高到哪去；
最终都靠基本法律去执行，
搞大新闻真来气！

蛤长者，忆往昔，
曾经作报告，后来当书记；
工程制图不容易啊，
坠痛苦是鸭嘴笔。

什么自我奋斗，什么历史推进；
实在不是谦虚，还望另请高明；
什么研究决定，什么调任北京；
苟利国家生死，岂因祸福避趋；
十分惭愧工作只是微小滴，
练就江胡的习气！

author: {'steamid': '76561197968911581', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 9, 'playtime_forever': 10404, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 4580, 'last_played': 1629255176}
review:
I will be the first to say as a 27 year old dad of a 5 year old I had very little expecations of this game; THIS GAME IS AMAZING!  

My son and I have sank 100+ hours into this game and still come back finding new adventures together.

- This game is HUGE.  There is so much to explore, so many things to unlock, and so many easter eggs to find!  This 
game is full of hidden gems throughout and I encourage you to explore the world for yourself without looking at guides.  Space environments, the zombie infested sewers, the fart gym, costumes, character customization, weapons, cars, blimps, and so much more will keep you coming back for more.  

- The local coop feature is amazing and I really love playing the game with my family!  My son is only able to play games with an Xbox controller so the controller support allows for easy couch coop action.  We regularly get a 3-4 player coop session going together and having an amazing sandbox to create adventures and stories with.  

- The game does take a semi-compentent machine to run the physics engine.  It is because almost every single object in the game has physics enabled and is able to be interacted with in someway.  The graphics, frog population density, and various other settings are completely open to being changed.


HIGHLY RECCOMEND this game for anyone looking for a fun quirky physics sandbox to explore.  The developers are both really cool dudes and their personality shows through the easter eggs found throughout the game.  I am always eager for their next update.  

Easily the best $20 I have spent in my lifetime for all of the memories we created with this game!  

Check out a sample of us goofing around to see just how much fun you can have!
(Amazing Frog? was the game that got us into doing a gaming channel together)

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E3loQuzMoKY

author: {'steamid': '76561198282983205', 'num_games_owned': 149, 'num_reviews': 42, 'playtime_forever': 36, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 36, 'last_played': 1488462955}
review:
请理智购买!
[spoiler]单纯想着+1s的蛤丝可无视该评测[/spoiler]
列举若干注意事项：
1.按键控制无法自定义，请在出生点Hideout房间内寻找左侧的控制说明。
2.笔记本个人测试结果：AMD-A10-5750M APU、Radeon HD8670M+HD8650G、8Gb内存的组合，配置在数据上达到要求，但FPS在11~85之间波动，在室外场景Swidon中平均只有20多帧，受场景大小影响较大。[spoiler]A卡用户自重[/spoiler]
3.画面偏亮，光影奇特，部分细节偏向美漫风，整体上风格杂乱。
4.人物动作少，易摔倒；倒地后可滑行；跳跃时难预判落脚点。物理缺乏真实感。
5.没找到存档，贴吧传言没有存档功能，未考证。
综上所述，这是一款完成度尚不高的游戏，缺少基本客制化系统，优化存在问题，游戏内容杂糅，物理真实性偏低。该游戏的乐趣，个人理解为探寻巨大的地图和众多有趣的细节，以及发挥想象自娱自乐。
最后，考虑到仅有两个开发者，对其工作表示敬意。期待将来能让这游戏变得更好。

[spoiler]已退款,这1s我续不了。留以后正式版本推出再考虑。[/spoiler]

author: {'steamid': '76561198267623481', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 42, 'playtime_forever': 1231, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 975, 'last_played': 1525618088}
review:
First off, let me just say this. Please, please add the online multiplayer in Unity 5 soon! I can't wait! Alright to business...

This is a good game for anyone under... lets say 17. Anywhere older and you may find this game as stupid as a potato with a knife stuck in it's top.

Pros:
-Funny gameplay
-Tons of easter eggs
-Huge city to explore and other stuff such as the sewers
-Different game modes (Zombies, sharks, racing rooms, kill rooms, etc) if you're bored of running around Swindon
-Farts
-Local player is good... But you need a controller for Player 2 and Player 3 and so on. Player 1 can use the keyboard/mouse.
-Grappling hooks
-GUNS
-Running away with frogs and arresting criminals
-Pigs you can ride and cars
-Large variety of clothes/accessories
-Lots of pros.


Now, lets get to the cons.
Cons:
-Outside of Swindon, there isn't much you can do
-Outside the wall, my landscape glitched and now all I can do is stay in the town/modes (May not happen for you)
-Falling down while running is funny but gets annoying fast
-Online multiplayer is yet to come
-Population of frogs in Swindon can't be too high or your frame rate drops drastically
-Hard to learn to play when you first join, it only gives you a board with controls, and no tutorial with scenarios.

8.5/10 would be Captain Frog again

review:
Have you ever thought your life was dull? Sought for adventure? Longed for a way to be what you always wished to be? Wanted to look better, be slimmer and have meaningful relationships?
Well... This game offers none of that. However you are a frog, and if you don't think that's far superior than you are a dire fool. Amzing Frog? is quite simply amazing...frog? If I could I would sell my nonexistant children and significant other just to think about buying this game again, because that is quite simply the greatest and most fufilling decision you can make in this life.
Some religious text speak of an amazing (frog?) afterlife, well this is the closest thing to that afterlife in our world. 
Do yourself a favour and buy three copies of this game. Thank me later.
Pros:
-Yes
Cons:
-

There are no downsides.

author: {'steamid': '76561198034124189', 'num_games_owned': 384, 'num_reviews': 17, 'playtime_forever': 214, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'last_played': 1482752697}
review:
At the moment, I really cannot reccomend Amazing Frog?. Although there are some interesting mechanics and worthwhile gameplay, it has yet to capitalize on itself. They've definitely made an interesting sandbox, and Swindon appears to be teeming with life at first glance, but after logging 4 hours, I had to get a refund. I've had this game on my wishlist for 2 years and have neever seen it on sale, but I decided to give it a go anyway, figuring it couldn't be the worst $16 I'd ever spend.

I really can't say that it's worth buying at the moment, unfortunately. There just isn't anything fun to do, after exploring the world. Picking up trash is suprisingly fun, but because you can only pick up one thing at a time, the movement is so slow, and trash receptacles are so spaced apart, it gets boring quickly. Searching for skins is fun, but the movement feels so broken and never does what I ask of it, it's almost unbearable. I understand the point of the movement is to be goofy and funny, but when a joke gets in the way of core mechanics that should be reliable, it's hard to take the game seriously. 

This review isn't very in-depth, but the takeaway here is that it's just not worth a $15 price tag, plus tax for a digital toy with no goals, no functionality, and is likely to never see the light of full release. If it was a $7.50 game, I absolutely would have recommended the game, for the 4 hours of play and laughs it provided; $16 with no vision of a full release and no sales is just unacceptable, in my eyes.

author: {'steamid': '76561198182576047', 'num_games_owned': 90, 'num_reviews': 52, 'playtime_forever': 9039, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 5108, 'last_played': 1703469861}
review:
Alright, Amazing Frog, lets go. Note, I'll be re-writing this review when the Unity 5 version is out.


Graphics - To be honest, the graphics in this game aren't great. Most things around the map have a low-poly model and a low res texture making some entire buildings look like nothing more than a colored cube. This is to be expected however, the game was originally built for the OUYA, which doesn't have the highest capacity, and the game is now being remade for the PC. Some buildings have been turned high quality, such as the swindon town planning office or the Frog Court. The lighting is kind of bland, objects dont react to light the way real ones should, and I'm pretty sure most of the lighting in the game is pre-baked. 6/10

Gameplay - What the game lacks in visuals, it makes up for in content. Theres a lot to do in swindon alone. Rescue cats, do a Time Trial, lock up robbers, collect costumes, etc. Outside of swindon theres a giant island with cool stuff to find here and there. Theres a blimp up in some mountains, and a beach with some sharks and cool boats. In the sewers, you can explore all the tunnels, fighting or running away from zombies, trying to find the legendary giant toilet, or trying to unlock a strange mysterious vault, which surely leads to something amazing... And if you ever get sick of Swindon, take a trip to the moon! Fill the rocket outside the warehouse with gas, and blast off! 9/10

The Community - This game has a really nice community of people who play it. Theres forums where you can ask questions if you need help with the game, or a discord if you just wanna chat with some fellow players. My only complaint about the community is that theres always one guy who asks if theres gonna be online multiplayer. The answer is yes, and I swear, no matter how many times anyone answers this question someones always gonna ask it again. I think I may or may not have been one of these people, I don't think I was, but I may have been. 9/10.

Overall - 8.5/10


Side note: the game won't be optimized to f0.3.0, so a lot of computers will lag horribly when playing this game... make sure you have a good computer

review:
Awesome game!

At first I was like, 'What the hell, all you do is run around, fart and fall over' but my daughter likes watching Pungeance on the tube, and I can't really let her play GTA5, so we kept playing...

And wow! once you figure out how things work, learn about some unlocks and start two player (Controllers highly recommended, camera moves much better with them) the hours will fly by. Getting some unlocks feel like genuine achievements / lessons in perseverance, the LOL key and microscopes spring to mind.

Zombies, pigs, cars, sharks, cops n robbers, Superheroes, Supervillains, farting, falling over, time trials, giant ants, Narnia, T.A.R.D.I.S, kittens, space ships, Segways, and trampolines, and all set in Swindon! fantastic fun.

review:
This is by far the best game I have ever played. The beautiful world of Swindon really comes alive in this one of a kind, open world sandbox game.  Despite the games amazingly life-like graphics, it is still cable of running on many mid range machines. It also has an amazing story line to match, as well as fun and immersive gameplay. This game is the perfect mixture of frog farts and sharks you never new you needed to complete your life. Until now, that is.

11/10 Best Game Ever.

author: {'steamid': '76561198114550950', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 11, 'playtime_forever': 3244, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 1973, 'last_played': 1579539005}
review:
Do you ever wish Grand Theft Auto V had local co-op? Do you ever wish you could push a giant button that magically spawns balloons? Do you ever wish you could hop into a blimp and fly away, only to lightly bump the side of a mountain, causing you to uncontrollably flip upside-down and explode? Do you wish you could do all that while being a bipedal frog dressed as the Dragonborn, or as the Joker, or Totoro, and also with a rocket launcher strapped to your back?
If you answered yes to at least one of these questions, then this, my friend, is the game for you.

review:
เกมนี้จะเป็นแนว Open World คล้ายๆ GTA แต่เป็นเวอร์ชั่นกบ Map นี่ใหญ่พอสมควรผมลองเปิดดูแล้ว แต่ส่วนมากจะเป็นป่าเป็นภูเขาซะส่วนใหญ่
พวกเมืองยังมีน้อยอยู่เพราะเป็นเกมอยู่ในช่วงพัฒนา แล้วก็เกมนี้เล่นด้วยกันได้ 4 คนเลยนะในเครื่องเดียวกัน ซึ่งใครสนใจก็ซื้อมาลองเดินเที่ยวเล่นกันก่อนได้ถึงเมืองจะยังมีน้อยก็เถอะ
ถ้าอยากได้เมืองเยอะๆ ก็ช่วยกันสนับสนุนกันเยอะๆ เผื่อทางผู้พัฒนาเขาจะได้มีกำลังใจพัฒนาต่อไป พอเขาเห็นว้าว เกมเรามีคนซื้อกันเยอะเว้ย รีบพัฒนาต่อไวๆ ดีกว่า ไม่ถึงเดือนเกมก็จะออกจากช่วงพัฒนากลายเป็นเกมเต็ม Map เต็มไปด้วยเมืองอันสวยงาม สภาพแวดล้อมดูสง่างาม 

(ไปและไปนอนฝันต่อ)

author: {'steamid': '76561198091991512', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 30, 'playtime_forever': 1194, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 390, 'last_played': 1494720762}
review:
This game is like a terrible version of Goat Simulator.
You can't sprint for more than five seconds without farting and falling on your face.
Walking on or off the curb of a sidewalk will make you go ragdoll and fall. 
Visually The game is ugly as sin and many of the textures such as building logos fail to render properly causing a flickering look. Most N64/PS1 games are prettier. 
The town is shamefully small and escaping its walls will provide little else to do but go to the beach . A town this small should be packed with personality and mini activities but i feel ripped of from lack of content.
My daughter wanted this game and she tends to enjoy its ridiculousness but I cringe when she gets me to play co-op as much as I love playing games with her. 
If open world physics-based nonsense is what you crave just stick with goats for now.

author: {'steamid': '76561197999042043', 'num_games_owned': 322, 'num_reviews': 59, 'playtime_forever': 273, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 120, 'last_played': 1534093390}
review: I still don't understand why we pay $15 for a game about nothing, where you do nothing, with incredibly frustrating controls. But my nephew really wanted to play it. Like, really really wanted to play it. He said it was the most fun....so...here we are...with $15 missing from my account, and a ridiculous game about nothing. But I guess it is entertainment. I guess if you like games like Goat Simulator and the like, where you just cause chaos that doesn't really amount to anything, then go ahead. Get this game. I feel weird recommending it...but, it does the trick.

review:
这游戏如水，可载舟，亦可赛艇啊！
在这款游戏中，包括了：
1.侠盗猎车手

author: {'steamid': '76561198065204318', 'num_games_owned': 961, 'num_reviews': 4, 'playtime_forever': 103, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 103, 'last_played': 1464417218}
review:
I really don't understand the positive reviews on this game at all. The map is incredibly barren, there's no online multiplayer, and theres nothing to do in the game even after you go through a stupidly hard jumping obstacle course just to unlock the privelege to have weapons. But thats not even the worst part about this game. The worst part is the incessant farting that your character does. It probably wouldnt be a problem if the frog JUST farted, but it doesnt JUST fart. It ragdolls. Every single time your frog farts, which is about every 10-20 seconds while youre running, your frog character trips on nothing and falls. So basically, running is slower than walking in this game because walking is the only way to prevent the farting. I've tried googling why in the world my frog is farting so much and why this farting causes my frog to fall, but no one else really seems to be bothered by this for some reason. Am I the only one with this problem? Genuine question. I haven't seen a single other person bothered by the fact that you cant run in a straight line for 15 seconds without falling down for no reason. 

Even without this horrible farting "mechanic," this game still wouldnt be that much fun at all. Maybe it might be fun for an hour or so with a friend, but this is only possible with split screen. The vehicles feel very clunky and slow, weapons are mostly pointless, and there is no real explanation as to what youre supposed to do or how to do it. This game is not at all worth $16. I might pay two or three dollars tops for this game. Once again, REALLY do not understand the "Very Positive" consensus from the steam community.

review:
This game is possibly one of the best comedic/dick-a-round-with-friends kind of game. 

For starters, it offers local splitscreen, and the ability to fart. Need I say more?
There's only 2 devs, but here's the thing: They are possibly one of the best dev teams. For example, I had asked them if they could implement a P2P networking element into the game for online play. Couple hours later, they're already working on adding it into the game. Not to mention, they also push out updates every 2-4 weeks adding new content and secrets to find, along with more stupid goofs and gaffs. 

All in all, I give this game a 10/10

author: {'steamid': '76561197994329352', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 5, 'playtime_forever': 594, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 367, 'last_played': 1708870641}
review:
I really wanted to like this game, i really did, but I can't. It doesn't work for me.

1) Graphics - there's lots of z-fighting going on, frustum culling is sometimes very visible. And so much is just butt-ugly, and there's certain very low-res textures. 
2) Gameplay - There's little to do and everything feels so empty. There's some good content, but it's not easy to find. You have to explore a lot (or look at youtube videos) to find the fun bits. 
3) Originality - It's goat simulator with fart & shark jokes (so called shart-jokes). As for now, Goat simulator is so much more fun, even though Amazing Frog? is promising on how it allows interaction with objects. Sadly I haven't seen one good usecase yet. 

Performance is so-so. It works on my (pretty dank) machine, but i sometimes the game freezes for up to a second. I can't seem to increase population density.

I can hardly imagine that the developers who made this are capable to implement the promised online-multiplayer and populate their huge-ass empty map with stuff without everything going to shit. While they seem motivated and full of ideas in their regular blog posts, their priorities seem to be a bit off...

Maybe this game is more fun with other players, but the technical fallacies are just too much of a turn-off for me.

review: I was so excited, I finally got the money for the game, however, I ended up paying $16 for a game that DOESNT WORK! My frog goes backwards when I hit "w", left when I hit "d" and so on so on. author: {'steamid': '76561198203174961', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 3, 'playtime_forever': 6021, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 3697, 'last_played': 1650223976}
review:
[i]Edited review on 6/3/2019[/i]

[i][h1]2019 review:[/h1][/i]

As of March 2019, the time had come to write a 2019 review for The Amazing Frog?.

Now I'm mainly a console gamer, and I rarely put any more than 60 hours into PC games. The Amazing Frog is one of those games that I put nearly 100 hours into, and that may not sound much for you reading this review, but for me that's the most amount of hours I have ever put into a PC game. The Amazing Frog is a game that will glue you to your screen once a new update drops. And that takes us to the biggest and most important con of this game: the amount of time you will have to wait until a new update drops. Fayju, a indie-game company, only has two employees (at the time of writing this review). It takes a lot of time for two developers to provide a big early access game of big updates. If you hate waiting long for new updates to release, you really shouldn't buy this game. But if you love playing this game in it's current state, finding easter eggs and secrets, collecting trophies, discovering the map and then leaving the game for a few months to come back when there is a new update, you will definitely fall in love with this game.

All in all, I think this is a great game for people who enjoyed goat simulator.

author: {'steamid': '76561198101081212', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 89, 'playtime_forever': 1512, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 125, 'last_played': 1681181235}
review:
When this game first released for the pc my computer was literal dogwater, and couldn't run this above 30 frames on the lowest settings at 1024x768. 

My computer is now substantially better but it's basically a 30 fps standard for what is now the "current/next" generation of games. I still can't break 30 most of the time at 1080p on the legacy build OR 3.0.

HOWEVER, Now that I'm capable of actually doing something with the game I'm very happy that I've gotten to experience what I've been missing out on all these years. 

Protip: if you can avoid guides do it, it's a lot more fun to just screw around and hope it goes somewhere.

author: {'steamid': '76561198012363945', 'num_games_owned': 2121, 'num_reviews': 409, 'playtime_forever': 1509, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 514, 'last_played': 1641139167}
review:
Game is coming along nicely. New stuff gets added every now and then. It will however probably be in Early Acces for quite some time. 

Fun game that is all about messing around with the environment. Fun game to play with the kids. (not too small ones though. 5+ ages)  

Those who are into achievements can skip this one and get Goat Sim. Also those who have done everything in goat sim might need to take a closer look before buying. This game might not tickle them the right way as this is way way different than goat sim despite both being games that are about messing around. 

Those who really should buy this? couch players - Just 2 players messing around and trying to get into seemingly impossible places is fun. If however there is zero chance of any kind of local MP then one need to think again or wait for steep discounts. It is not bad going solo but the best fun is definitely local multiplayer.

author: {'steamid': '76561198068039882', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 16, 'playtime_forever': 6852, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 3676, 'last_played': 1703178509}
review:
Read full recommendation here: http://steamcommunity.com/groups/TheZeronShow/discussions/6/365163686066869387/

[i]* Some facts about the game are subject to change, keep in mind the date the recommendation was posted.
** This should be considered as a simple recommendation, not a full review. When the game enters a feature-complete state (final version), a detailed review will be posted.[/i]


Pros:
- Great game to play with friends (up to 4 players)
- Huge open-world map (about 20 sq.km)
- To date, the best virtual rendition of Swindon
- Unique concept
- Variety of vehicles that will expand
- Hard working and passionate developers
- The physics of the game can provide you hours of laughter
- Impressive for a game that's not yet finished
- Loads of costumes and other collectables to find
- Great community
- Many references in the game of multiple community members and youtubers
- Plenty of easter eggs and references
- Many things to do, infinite possibilities of making your own games with friends
- The only cons are things that will be fixed
- They just keep adding stuff and improving the game

Cons:
- Still retains some old textures from the OUYA version (will be replaced in future versions)
- Physics can be very glitchy sometimes
- No online support right now (but it will be implemented in the future)
- Despite the huge map, there isn't much going on in most areas
- At the moment, you will need a good computer to run Amazing Frog at normal FPS (will be optimized later)

Pros/Cons (depending on the player):
- Royalty free music by Kevin MacLeod
- High emphasis on toilet humor
- Cartoonish graphics

author: {'steamid': '76561198080063269', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 34, 'playtime_forever': 1254, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 373, 'last_played': 1655862029}
review:
Imagine Goat Simulator, but instead of everything being broken on purpose, the developers made sure that everything actually worked.

And that's what Amazing Frog? is. It seems dumb (and it [i]is[/i] dumb), but the game is quite a bit of fun.

[b]Everything actually working[/b] is important for a few reasons. For one, you're not fighting the game's lack of functionality when trying to accomplish something; and more importantly, the game has more to it other than a cheap joke. After all, a functional game needs to be good since it can't just pass by on some [i]"roflmao"[/i]s from the easily amused.

The game's developers (all two of them) are staying on top of updates too. Even if the updates are a bit infrequent due to the small team, the updates are very good. Every update so far has added at least  a little bit of new content, along with the usual tweaks and fixes.

review:
In truth, I liked the game, but it would be boring if the developers have not added new patches (including new locations in the game).
[h1] PROS [/h1]
+A frog, a very crooked and awkward you play like a slug is not able to walk normally, that is laughable.
+Graphics and a decent antialiasing
The presence of the phone (there are many apps that have half open.)
+Music and sounds cool
+Riding on about 15 modes of transport
+Easter eggs (Yes, they are!)
+5 types of trampolines
+Weapons
+NPC (which got stoned until the end of)
+Explosive barrels and substances
+Zombies and sharks (the only thing that can kill you, and write Wasted?)
+Pretty big not template world
+In the city almost all buildings can be entered
+Access to user and test maps
[h1] CONS [/h1]
-A lot of number of bugs
-No save 
-With optimization it seems everything is normal, but there are still places strange friezes
-Due to the clumsiness of the frog sometimes annoying to press Ctrl
-Transport is not very realistic, in the sense it is impossible to move normally
-WHERE THE CO-OP MODE !?
[u] 8.5/10 [/u]

review:
Der Name sagt alles, dieses Spiel ist Amazing!
Unmengen zu erkunden/erleben/erledigen, trotz sehr einfach gehaltener Grafik.
Egal wie lang die aktuelle Spielzeit ist, man  endeckt immer etwas neues oder erlebt etwas neues.
Das Spiel wird regelmäßig mit aufregenden Updates erweitert und die Entwickler antworten z.B.: Auf Twitter/Youtube schnellstens auf Fragen jeglicher Art.Klare Kaufempfehlung für Personen die: Open World, Witziges/Spannendes/Erlebnisreiche, Spiltscreen, Couch-Coop Spiele lieben.
(Bis jetzt das beste Spiel das man mit Freunden (Splitscreen) finden kann und sehr nette/aktive Entwickler.)

author: {'steamid': '76561198130404415', 'num_games_owned': 692, 'num_reviews': 19, 'playtime_forever': 106, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 106, 'last_played': 1453897865}
review:
Wie jemand schon mal erwähnte, wäre es gut, wenn es hier eine naja-wertung geben würde. 
Ich habe dieses Spiel gekauft , weil ich erwartete, etwas ähnliches wie Goat Simulator anzutreffen. Im nachhinein muss ich sagen: Ich habe mich getäuscht. Grosser Kritikpunkt: Es ist nichts los in der Welt, obwohl doch mittlerweile einiges so aussieht, als hätte es Potenzial spannend zu werden. Man läuft lange durch die Gegend, fällt oft einfach hin, meistens dauernd, weil der Frosch an irgendetwas anstösst und das war’s. Gut, dass war etwas überspitzt gesagt aber im grossen und Ganzen trifft es den schon den Kern der Angelegenheit. Ein paar lustige Dinge bzw. Easter Eggs gibt es, aber das hält nicht lange an, es wird fad und der Spieler verliert die Neugier. Etwas Abwechslung bieten da die Testing Rooms. Ich würde das Spiel zum jetzigen Zeitpunkt nicht weiter empfehlen, zumindest nicht zu dem Preis ( z.B. vergleich Goat Simulator kostet 10,- Amazing Frog 16.- -Franken-). Lieber warten bis sich mehr entwickelt hat oder zum reduzierten Preis kaufen. 

Zusammenfassend kann man sagen: Zu teuer für das was im Moment angeboten wird an Inhalt. Schade ist das Potenzial existiert, sich aber gefühlsmässig nur schleichend voran bewegt. Achievements könnten sicher Abhilfe schaffen, da der Spieler dann länger ans Spiel gebunden ist und die Neugier evt. geweckt wird. Auch kann ich mir vorstellen das Multiplayer noch einmal lustiger ist als Singleplayer, denn da kann man sich ja gegenseitig unterhalten.

author: {'steamid': '76561198256076312', 'num_games_owned': 220, 'num_reviews': 40, 'playtime_forever': 3291, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 1815, 'last_played': 1667332495}
review:
[i] Sits down. [/i] 
Well, time to review another game.
Oh, The Amazing Frog? You want me to review that?
Here we go.

One of my favourite games ever. There is just so much to do in this game! From performing a frog massacre with a flamethrower water gun,  to bouncing on a trampoline to space, spraying coffee on Joker Frog, "Working out" in the fart gyms and fighting off a horde of zombie frogs, oh, and sharks, they huuuuuunnngggrrry.
But wait! There's more.
The game now looks not good and the graphics aren't the best, but soon, the will be releasing a better, upgraded version of the game on Unity 5 (Good stuff) and will also come with online multiplayer. So when that comes, it'll be like christmas morning.

Now, there's LOTS i've missed off but I can't think and i'm lazy.
So, Amazing Frog? Set in Swindon in the UK, made by two legends, Gaz and Hal, I give this a Fart/10.
Did I say you can fart on people?

It says this was originally publish 24th January 2016 but I don't remember posting a review then, so this review should be up to date on the 18th February 2018 I think.

author: {'steamid': '76561198113615849', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 33, 'playtime_forever': 1034, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 464, 'last_played': 1697275736}
review:
"Me volveria a hechar un ped0"
-IGN 10/10

"Tus nalgas"
-Danielogs 9.99/10


Después de jugar a los juegos de Fayju como el Frog Box cuando era niño y ahora darme cuenta que sacaron otro juego de ranas, Deberas, Gaz tiene un problema con las ranas.."Amazing Frog?" Un juego que te permite hacer realidad tu sueño mas profundo, ser una rana.
Pero no cualquier rana, estamos hablando de la increíble Rana/sapo!
Pungence y Zeron tienen un nuevo contrincante, tú. Tienes que ser el Rana-alcalde de la ciudad maravillosa de Swindon. Pero no será fácil, tendrás que subir tu SCP primero.
Ya enserio... Amazing Frog o para los shavos; Grand Theft Rana o Grand Theft Frog es un juego divertido, un Goat Simulator pero con una Rana. Aunque aquí los desarrolladores son mas unidos con la comunidad. Este juego no esta completado al 100 pero con actualizaciones que según esto son mensuales, estarán añadiendo mas contenido y hasta pueden añadir cosas que tu les pidas! (Si es una buena idea claro..).
Sin duda, ameisinc frot es un juego que recomiendo mucho.
Cosas que me gustaría ver en el juego:
-Dinosaurios (Montables y enemigos)
-Multijugador Online (Aunque ya va a salir..)
-Mas vida en la ciudad PORFAVOR!
-Unas gráficas como en el OUYA
-Mas cosas en el mapa (Afuera de Swindon esta demasiado V A C Í O)
-Mas mapas, o mas modos de juegos como en el GTA
-Un modo historia o misiones
-Tener el poder de nadar bien PORFAVOR
-Saltar mas chido
-básicamente un GTA limitado, basado en ranas, y online.

Mi opinión:
Gráficas: 7
Jugabilidad: 7
Exploración: 5
Experiencia: 8

Sé que me eh pasado muchas cosas del juego pero lo recomiendo y el resultado final eeess.... 7/10 :,v
🐸
PD: Pa que quieres saber eso jaja saludos
PD2: Goatrix esta en el juego y YO NO?!

author: {'steamid': '76561198108397210', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 4, 'playtime_forever': 1604, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 1207, 'last_played': 1482035153}
review:
Definitely rate this game a 10/10. I bought this game when i think it was like really early access and now it has come a long ways. I like the graphics how they are cartoons and it just really fits the game. It can be a little tedious trying to get around the huge map but there is a lot of secrets in the game, and I think that Fayju has a few more tricks up their sleeves. Right now, you can find different costumes for your frog in the game, secret doors, and buttons as well. I don't want to spoil the game, so ill just say a little bit more about it. I think there is good and bad things about this game.

Good:
Very Intertaining
Many things to discover
NPCs actually kind of interact with you
there is cars and guns ;D
The map is HUGE
and much more!

Bad:
I find that the sharks get annoying after awhile
the map is big and it takes forever to get to place to place
The map could use some more towns and trees etc

Thats all from me, Enjoy Amazing Frog? :D

review:
Well, my own very biased opinion is that this game is just about the best thing that has ever existed. However, there are a few things that you should know. 

The game is not a serious game. If you are looking for a challenge, story, or a super polished game in general, this is not it. It is, however, fun if you would just like to mess around and explore a large map full of secrets. Its super fun to explore all of the fun stuff hidden, and will probably make you laugh a couple of times, especially if you are playing with friends. The game is also, as previously mentioned, not very polished. The graphics aren't great, but definitely not cringe worthy bad. It also runs pretty slowly, especially with split screen. Playing by myself I get a decent FPS on my average power computer. But it can get pretty slow while playing with friends. (I suggest turning the graphic settings down. Lastly, the game designers are committed to their game and very active in the community. Somewhat frequent updates with always hilarious or fun content, and they almost always answer your questions. 

All in all, the amount to pay for this game is a bit of a stretch, but if you can I suggest buying this game, if it is your type of game (Goofy sandbox) If you are short on cash, maybe wait until the game is more developed, by the way they plan on making it an online multiplayer game soon! So yeah. I'm really bad at ending things, so I guess i'll just say I really love this game.

review: This game is pretty freakin' amazing. I love this game because it's ridiculous. I love games that seem to have no point to them. There are many things to do in this game, but in my opinion, it's a lot more fun when you have at least one other person to play with. There aren't too many maps at the moment, but some of those maps are gigantic and have tons of fun things that you can interact with. There is no storyline to this game. You just play as a humanoid frog with weird physics. You can pick up all sorts of items or weapons like RPGs or machine guns. You can also drive vehicles like vans and boats. This game is a ton of fun if you like random stuff being all over the place.

author: {'steamid': '76561198025182878', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 19, 'playtime_forever': 6444, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 183, 'last_played': 1529706775}
review:
Ragdoll so much you will think your playing the insurance fraud side mission in saints row 4, but you wont get any bonus for the ragdoll...

Im not sure if I can recommend this game or not. Its a great concept and is kind of fun, but leads to be boring after a short time. It can be funny and make you laugh but it can also just drag. After only 1.5 hours of playtime I am not sure I will play again until the next update. My 4 year old even got bored of it after a while. While I can certainly appreciate the open world sandbox experience, it doesnt feel like it is fully there as of yet. I'm certain there are things outside of the city to find, however its a drag if you flip your car upsidedown and are stuck out there trying to search on foot - you end up spending a very long time just walking back to find another car or even just walking to -- nowhere really. It feels empty and barron outside the city walls and there doesnt seem like there is really much to do inside the city either (except for fall down over and over).

The mechanics feel clunky as well which is another thing that was really aggrivating to me. Walk up a curb fall down, walk to a wall fall down, walk to a door fall down, walk to a car door - fall down, even walking to an object results in getting knocked to the ground. I'm not sure if this is how the physics are supposed to work or not at this point and being I never played the previous version I dont know much about the game, but constant ragdoll when trying to walk to a object or even a NPC is very annoying to me. 

I saw a bunch of stuff in the videos and update news but cant seem to find them in game. Rocket Launcher?? Where is it? Fly a blimp, uh how and where?? Just thinking that the game is not very intuitive on letting players know where things are at, I mean I know there are things to find outside the walls of the city, but who wants to drive for 10 minutes somewhere, flip the car upside down then have to walk for 20 minutes though empty fields to find a freakin boat because there is no way to flip the car back upright??

Also the game needs some background music, all you hear outside of radios in the area is the frogs feet slapping against the ground as you walk. While I give it a +1 for creative thinking there some ambient music would be nice - the silent slapping of the frogs feet I feel contributes to making it feel more bland.

All in all the experience so far is OK, not great/amazing and not totally awful. I am going to recommend this game to sucker more people that skim over this review into buying the game so that maybe they will give some ideas in the forum and help make the game better.

Pros:
*Funny character 
*Large world
*Great for kids (until they get bored too)
*Developers are very active in the community
*Sharks
*A frog with a gun that can drive cars!!
*Local coop is fun

Cons:
*Lots of space without much to do
*Clunky physics result in falling down alot
*Not very intuitive - at least give me a hint on where I can go to find things to do
*Wheres all the stuff from the videos??
*Needs a music option
*Lots of graphical glitches

author: {'steamid': '76561198065911929', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 4, 'playtime_forever': 727, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 587, 'last_played': 1449291396}
review:
[h1] Seven years later... [/h1]
It's been 7 years since I wrote this review. You won't be shocked to know:
[olist]
    [*]It's still "Early Access" [i]BS alert[/i]
    [*]It's only marginally less empty and boring than it was 7 years ago
    [*]It costs 5 dollars [i]more[/i] than it did 7 years ago
[/olist]
My hope in this was misplaced. "Early Access" is at its worst here: an excuse to sell an incomplete game forever. Just release similarly incomplete "V2", "V3", ... to renew the excuse at a higher price. Genius

[hr][/hr]
[i](Original 2015 review)[/i]

This game is definitely not worth its price yet. Still very buggy, slow, and it feels barren and quiet. Outside of Swindon, gameplay is dull and it takes forever to get nowhere. A pain to play and the longer I play the more I feel that I'm absolutely wasting my time. This game isn't worth more than $0.99 in its current state, and the final product'll be worth less than $5. I regret my purchase (for now), but hope this game will become something with lasting playability.

author: {'steamid': '76561198166775590', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 58, 'playtime_forever': 1478, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 881, 'last_played': 1569983132}
review:
In my opinion, Amazing Frog? is worth the $15.99 for many great reasons, and here they are.

Pros:

Fun and crazy gameplay
Lots of hidden secrets
Split screen with friends is  even better and funnyer
You're a frog
You can ride pigs
Insane bouncing off trampolines
EVEN CRAZIER BOUNCING WHILE RIDING A PIG
The bugs and glitches are funny (sometimes)
You can make your frog all swaggy with the wardrobe in game
This game is great even though its in early access

I would list off the cons, but they are mostly stuff that is going to be added in the next update XD

What I would like to see:

Online multiplayer
More cars (like super cars, monster trucks, etc.)
Workshop content (like custom maps/worlds, custom frogs and clothes, etc.)
More big cities
fixing a bug i only see in split screen, which is that the pigs will glitch out and start to jump back or sideways. (pls fix, it breaks the pigs)
Rideable whales that you can find in the water, and travel moderatly fast
Melee weapons
A sandbox mode, where you can make your own cities and creations (that could possibly be put on the workshop)
Some more clothes in the wardrobe ( I know that it is in alpha right now)
Grenades and other throwable weapons

Those are just some ideas I came up with, but as long as Amazing Frog? continues to grow, I will be a fan of this epic game, that is all.

author: {'steamid': '76561198072379832', 'num_games_owned': 540, 'num_reviews': 6, 'playtime_forever': 384, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 247, 'last_played': 1456676799}
review:
※1/19現在、お布施目的やカエルがアサルトライフルをぶっ放したり、豚に乗って街を散歩したり、高いところに屁をこきながら吹っ飛んでいく姿を見て繰り返し楽しめるAmazing man以外は購入をおすすめできません。


このゲームは最近のシミュレーター系のゲームと比べても現状遊べる要素がほとんどないです
まず目標やコレクションアイテムもないですし、街も非常に狭くハリボテ、明確なルールをもったミニゲームもないです
操作性も非常に悪くすぐ転びます、道路と歩道の間の段差や階段もまともに登れません

ですが、このゲームはネタゲーとして作られているわけではなく
もっと広いオープンワールドの世界をオンラインで遊べるサンドボックスゲー、GTA likeなゲームをめざして開発されています
つまり、かなり初期の段階のゲームを、買うのを躊躇うような値段設定でテスター募集している状態ということです

ゾンビCOOPや、PVP、レースなどのテストMAP、アップデートなどの開発者のこだわりに期待せざるを得ないのでおすすめ評価を押させていただきます

author: {'steamid': '76561198048952647', 'num_games_owned': 290, 'num_reviews': 4, 'playtime_forever': 1354, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 1091, 'last_played': 1668857934}
review:
Ich liebe dieses Spiel!

Ich habe es damals in einem Pewdiepie Video gesehen und war ziemlich begeistert. Musste dann leider feststellen das es Ouya Exklusiv war. Nun ist es für Steam erschienen und ich bin wirklich froh dieses Spiel gekauft zu haben. Zwar bietet es noch nicht den selben Umfang wie die Ouya Version, aber bietet jetzt schon eine Menge Spaß. Man sollte dies aber mindestens zu zweit spielen! Es war jeden Cent Wert und ich würde es sofort wieder kaufen. 
Jeder der Open-World Spiele mag und auf Entdeckungstour gehen will, wird dieses Spiel lieben. Es macht zwar anfänglich den anschein als wenn man noch nichts zu tun hat, aber wenn man jeder Kleinigkeit nachgeht wird man belohnt! Und wenn man nur ein Keks bekommt XD
Der aktuelle Stand bietet einiges für 2 Spieler: Schach, Fußball, Basketball, Rennen, Zombies, viel Easter Eggs zum entdecken, Explosionen, verschiedene Kostüme, und natürlich genug Möglichkeiten das Spiel auf dem Kopf zustellen.

Update: In der zwischenzeit hat sich eine Menge getan und macht mir nun mehr Spaß als je zuvor. Ich bin schon gespannt was als nächstes dazu kommt.

Das Beste sind die Platschenden geräusche beim Laufen xD

author: {'steamid': '76561198014932334', 'num_games_owned': 2698, 'num_reviews': 55, 'playtime_forever': 520, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 33, 'last_played': 1533507154}
review:
It's early days. Not even at the level of the Ouya version, runs kinda badly, and doesn't have a lot of content. But! It's still a goofy sandbox with weird physics and unexplainable antics, local co-op, and weird secrets, which is exactly why anyone would buy this.

The genre is a recent breed of game that aims for social hilarity and player goal-set concepts. Amazing Frog? is actually enjoyable here as opposed to being animated gif fodder for the unfunny basements of the internet. The humor (mostly fart or "why is there a grill here" related) remains low-key, amusing throughout and the wacky nature of the game never distracts from the 3D platforming.

The PC version obviously needs a lot of tweaks to reach the level of its Ouya twin but I have no doubt that most will find the game not only fun now but holds the promise of more fun after support from the developer progresses.

author: {'steamid': '76561197971872021', 'num_games_owned': 4894, 'num_reviews': 40, 'playtime_forever': 2832, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 913, 'last_played': 1700958590}
review:
As someone who has played countless hours of this game on Ouya, I'm SUPER excited this is finally on Steam!

Amazing Frog is a quirky-physics sandbox game. The amount of enjoyment you will get out of it will depend a lot on how much you can provide your own entertainment. There are trampolines, vehicles, cannons, trampolines, ramps, and other objects strewn throughout the world. It's a playground of items with near-limitless potential.

In the transition from Ouya they've made the world MUCH larger and removed the odd pricing scheme for level access, opting for a flat rate. I think $15 is more than fair for the amount of time you'll get out of this discovering items, screwing around with friends, and having a good time. The game doesn't bring much to the table if you're playing alone; playing with at least one other person is best.

My few disappointments are the lack of availability for weapons (there were many more readily available in the Ouya version), and that the game no longer appears to outline where the other players are on the map. On the Ouya version you would see an outline of the other players wherever they were on the map. The settings menu is SLIGHTLY confusing because when you choose "Fantastic" for graphics it appears to accept but reflects "Fast" in the menu anyway. I'd chalk that up to a glitch.

All-told, it's GREAT fun for local co-op and I'd recommend it to anyone that wants to have a great couple hours with friends just messing around.

Edit: 1/19/19, They've certainly added more weapons and TONS more stuff to do. The graphics glitch has also been fixed. I absolutely love this game, and so does everyone I introduce it to!
